317  //**Constructor*********************************************************************************
323  explicit inline DMatTDMatMultExpr( const MT1& lhs, const MT2& rhs ) noexcept
324  : lhs_( lhs ) // Left-hand side dense matrix of the multiplication expression
325  , rhs_( rhs ) // Right-hand side dense matrix of the multiplication expression
326  {
327  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( lhs.columns() == rhs.rows(), "Invalid matrix sizes" );
328  }
329  //**********************************************************************************************
330 
331  //**Access operator*****************************************************************************
338  inline ReturnType operator()( size_t i, size_t j ) const {
339  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( i < lhs_.rows() , "Invalid row access index" );
340  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( j < rhs_.columns(), "Invalid column access index" );
341 
342  if( IsDiagonal<MT1>::value ) {
343  return lhs_(i,i) * rhs_(i,j);
344  }
345  else if( IsDiagonal<MT2>::value ) {
346  return lhs_(i,j) * rhs_(j,j);
347  }
348  else if( IsTriangular<MT1>::value || IsTriangular<MT2>::value ) {
349  const size_t begin( ( IsUpper<MT1>::value )
350  ?( ( IsLower<MT2>::value )
351  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT1>::value ? i+1UL : i )
352  , ( IsStrictlyLower<MT2>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
353  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT1>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
354  :( ( IsLower<MT2>::value )
355  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT2>::value ? j+1UL : j )
356  :( 0UL ) ) );
357  const size_t end( ( IsLower<MT1>::value )
358  ?( ( IsUpper<MT2>::value )
359  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT1>::value ? i : i+1UL )
360  , ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT2>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
361  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT1>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
362  :( ( IsUpper<MT2>::value )
363  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT2>::value ? j : j+1UL )
364  :( lhs_.columns() ) ) );
365 
366  if( begin >= end ) return ElementType();
367 
368  const size_t n( end - begin );
369 
370  return subvector( row( lhs_, i ), begin, n ) * subvector( column( rhs_, j ), begin, n );
371  }
372  else {
373  return row( lhs_, i ) * column( rhs_, j );
374  }
375  }
376  //**********************************************************************************************
377 
378  //**At function*********************************************************************************
386  inline ReturnType at( size_t i, size_t j ) const {
387  if( i >= lhs_.rows() ) {
388  BLAZE_THROW_OUT_OF_RANGE( "Invalid row access index" );
389  }
390  if( j >= rhs_.columns() ) {
391  BLAZE_THROW_OUT_OF_RANGE( "Invalid column access index" );
392  }
393  return (*this)(i,j);
394  }
395  //**********************************************************************************************
396 
397  //**Rows function*******************************************************************************
402  inline size_t rows() const noexcept {
403  return lhs_.rows();
404  }
405  //**********************************************************************************************
406 
407  //**Columns function****************************************************************************
412  inline size_t columns() const noexcept {
413  return rhs_.columns();
414  }
415  //**********************************************************************************************
416 
417  //**Left operand access*************************************************************************
422  inline LeftOperand leftOperand() const noexcept {
423  return lhs_;
424  }
425  //**********************************************************************************************
426 
427  //**Right operand access************************************************************************
432  inline RightOperand rightOperand() const noexcept {
433  return rhs_;
434  }

446  }

458  }

479  ( rows() * columns() >= SMP_DMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD );
480  }

489  //**Assignment to dense matrices****************************************************************
502  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
503  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
504  friend inline void assign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
505  {
506  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
507 
508  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
509  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
510 
511  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL ) {
512  return;
513  }
514  else if( rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
515  reset( ~lhs );
516  return;
517  }
518 
519  LT A( serial( rhs.lhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
520  RT B( serial( rhs.rhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
521 
522  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
523  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
524  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
525  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
526  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
527  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
528 
529  DMatTDMatMultExpr::selectAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B );
530  }
532  //**********************************************************************************************
533 
534  //**Assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)*********************************************
545  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
546  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
547  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
548  static inline void selectAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
549  {
550  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value || IsDiagonal<MT5>::value ) ||
551  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < DMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
552  selectSmallAssignKernel( C, A, B );
553  else
554  selectBlasAssignKernel( C, A, B );
555  }
557  //**********************************************************************************************
558 
559  //**Default assignment to row-major dense matrices (general/general)****************************
573  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
574  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
575  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
576  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
577  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
578  {
579  const size_t M( A.rows() );
580  const size_t N( B.columns() );
581  const size_t K( A.columns() );
582 
583  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
584 
585  const size_t ibegin( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
586  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value && M > 1UL ) ? 2UL : 1UL )
587  :( 0UL ) );
588  const size_t iend( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
589  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value && M > 1UL ) ? M-2UL : M-1UL )
590  :( M ) );
591  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
592 
593  for( size_t i=0UL; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
594  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j ) {
595  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
596  }
597  }
598  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i )
599  {
600  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value )
601  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
602  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+2UL : i+1UL )
603  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
604  :( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )
605  ?( SYM || HERM || UPP ? max( i, 1UL ) : 1UL )
606  :( SYM || HERM || UPP ? i : 0UL ) ) );
607  const size_t jend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value )
608  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
609  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i-1UL : i )
610  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
611  :( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value )
612  ?( LOW ? min(i+1UL,N-1UL) : N-1UL )
613  :( LOW ? i+1UL : N ) ) );
614 
615  if( ( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) && ( jbegin > jend ) ) {
616  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j ) {
617  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
618  }
619  continue;
620  }
621 
622  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
623 
624  for( size_t j=( SYM || HERM ? i : 0UL ); j<jbegin; ++j ) {
625  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
626  }
627  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jend; ++j )
628  {
629  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
630  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
631  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
632  , ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
633  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
634  :( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
635  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
636  :( 0UL ) ) );
637  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
638  ?( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
639  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
640  , ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
641  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
642  :( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
643  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
644  :( K ) ) );
645  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin < kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
646 
647  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,kbegin) * B(kbegin,j);
648  for( size_t k=kbegin+1UL; k<kend; ++k ) {
649  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
650  }
651  }
652  for( size_t j=jend; j<N; ++j ) {
653  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
654  }
655  }
656  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
657  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j ) {
658  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
659  }
660  }
661 
662  if( SYM || HERM ) {
663  for( size_t i=1UL; i<M; ++i ) {
664  for( size_t j=0UL; j<i; ++j ) {
665  (~C)(i,j) = HERM ? conj( (~C)(j,i) ) : (~C)(j,i);
666  }
667  }
668  }
669  }
671  //**********************************************************************************************
672 
673  //**Default assignment to column-major dense matrices (general/general)*************************
687  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
688  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
689  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
690  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
691  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
692  {
693  const size_t M( A.rows() );
694  const size_t N( B.columns() );
695  const size_t K( A.columns() );
696 
697  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
698 
699  const size_t jbegin( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )
700  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value && N > 1UL ) ? 2UL : 1UL )
701  :( 0UL ) );
702  const size_t jend( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value )
703  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value && N > 1UL ) ? N-2UL : N-1UL )
704  :( N ) );
705  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
706 
707  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jbegin; ++j ) {
708  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i ) {
709  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
710  }
711  }
712  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jend; ++j )
713  {
714  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value )
715  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
716  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+2UL : j+1UL )
717  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
718  :( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
719  ?( SYM || HERM || LOW ? max( j, 1UL ) : 1UL )
720  :( SYM || HERM || LOW ? j : 0UL ) ) );
721  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value )
722  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
723  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )?( j-1UL ):( j ) )
724  :( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )?( j ):( j+1UL ) ) )
725  :( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
726  ?( UPP ? min(j+1UL,M-1UL) : M-1UL )
727  :( UPP ? j+1UL : M ) ) );
728 
729  if( ( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) && ( ibegin > iend ) ) {
730  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i ) {
731  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
732  }
733  continue;
734  }
735 
736  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
737 
738  for( size_t i=( SYM || HERM ? j : 0UL ); i<ibegin; ++i ) {
739  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
740  }
741  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i )
742  {
743  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
744  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
745  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
746  , ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
747  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
748  :( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
749  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
750  :( 0UL ) ) );
751  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
752  ?( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
753  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
754  , ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
755  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
756  :( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
757  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
758  :( K ) ) );
759  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin < kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
760 
761  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,kbegin) * B(kbegin,j);
762  for( size_t k=kbegin+1UL; k<kend; ++k ) {
763  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
764  }
765  }
766  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
767  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
768  }
769  }
770  for( size_t j=jend; j<N; ++j ) {
771  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i ) {
772  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
773  }
774  }
775 
776  if( SYM || HERM ) {
777  for( size_t j=1UL; j<N; ++j ) {
778  for( size_t i=0UL; i<j; ++i ) {
779  (~C)(i,j) = HERM ? conj( (~C)(j,i) ) : (~C)(j,i);
780  }
781  }
782  }
783  }
785  //**********************************************************************************************
786 
787  //**Default assignment to row-major dense matrices (general/diagonal)***************************
801  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
802  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
803  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
804  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
805  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
806  {
807  const size_t M( A.rows() );
808  const size_t N( B.columns() );
809 
810  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i )
811  {
812  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
813  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
814  :( 0UL ) );
815  const size_t jend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
816  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
817  :( N ) );
818  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
819 
820  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
821  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jbegin; ++j ) {
822  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
823  }
824  }
825  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jend; ++j ) {
826  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,j) * B(j,j);
827  }
828  if( IsLower<MT4>::value ) {
829  for( size_t j=jend; j<N; ++j ) {
830  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
831  }
832  }
833  }
834  }
836  //**********************************************************************************************
837 
838  //**Default assignment to column-major dense matrices (general/diagonal)************************
852  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
853  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
854  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
855  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
856  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
857  {
858  constexpr size_t block( BLOCK_SIZE );
859 
860  const size_t M( A.rows() );
861  const size_t N( B.columns() );
862 
863  for( size_t jj=0UL; jj<N; jj+=block ) {
864  const size_t jend( min( N, jj+block ) );
865  for( size_t ii=0UL; ii<M; ii+=block ) {
866  const size_t iend( min( M, ii+block ) );
867  for( size_t j=jj; j<jend; ++j )
868  {
869  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
870  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j ), ii ) )
871  :( ii ) );
872  const size_t ipos( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
873  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL ), iend ) )
874  :( iend ) );
875 
876  if( IsLower<MT4>::value ) {
877  for( size_t i=ii; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
878  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
879  }
880  }
881  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; ++i ) {
882  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,j) * B(j,j);
883  }
884  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
885  for( size_t i=ipos; i<iend; ++i ) {
886  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
887  }
888  }
889  }
890  }
891  }
892  }
894  //**********************************************************************************************
895 
896  //**Default assignment to row-major dense matrices (diagonal/general)***************************
910  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
911  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
912  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
913  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
914  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
915  {
916  constexpr size_t block( BLOCK_SIZE );
917 
918  const size_t M( A.rows() );
919  const size_t N( B.columns() );
920 
921  for( size_t ii=0UL; ii<M; ii+=block ) {
922  const size_t iend( min( M, ii+block ) );
923  for( size_t jj=0UL; jj<N; jj+=block ) {
924  const size_t jend( min( N, jj+block ) );
925  for( size_t i=ii; i<iend; ++i )
926  {
927  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
928  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+1UL : i ), jj ) )
929  :( jj ) );
930  const size_t jpos( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
931  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i : i+1UL ), jend ) )
932  :( jend ) );
933 
934  if( IsUpper<MT5>::value ) {
935  for( size_t j=jj; j<jbegin; ++j ) {
936  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
937  }
938  }
939  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jpos; ++j ) {
940  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,i) * B(i,j);
941  }
942  if( IsLower<MT5>::value ) {
943  for( size_t j=jpos; j<jend; ++j ) {
944  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
945  }
946  }
947  }
948  }
949  }
950  }
952  //**********************************************************************************************
953 
954  //**Default assignment to column-major dense matrices (diagonal/general)************************
968  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
969  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
970  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
971  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
972  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
973  {
974  const size_t M( A.rows() );
975  const size_t N( B.columns() );
976 
977  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
978  {
979  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
980  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
981  :( 0UL ) );
982  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
983  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
984  :( M ) );
985  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
986 
987  if( IsLower<MT5>::value ) {
988  for( size_t i=0UL; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
989  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
990  }
991  }
992  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
993  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,i) * B(i,j);
994  }
995  if( IsUpper<MT5>::value ) {
996  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
997  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
998  }
999  }
1000  }
1001  }
1003  //**********************************************************************************************
1004 
1005  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/diagonal)************************************
1019  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1020  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1021  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1022  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
1023  selectDefaultAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1024  {
1025  reset( C );
1026 
1027  for( size_t i=0UL; i<A.rows(); ++i ) {
1028  C(i,i) = A(i,i) * B(i,i);
1029  }
1030  }

1033 
1034  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (small matrices)***************************************
1048  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1049  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1050  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1051  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1052  selectSmallAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1053  {
1054  selectDefaultAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1055  }
1057  //**********************************************************************************************
1058 
1059  //**Vectorized default assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)******************
1074  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1075  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1076  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1077  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1078  selectSmallAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1079  {
1080  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
1081 
1082  const size_t M( A.rows() );
1083  const size_t N( B.columns() );
1084  const size_t K( A.columns() );
1085 
1086  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
1087 
1088  if( LOW && UPP ) {
1089  reset( ~C );
1090  }
1091 
1092  {
1093  size_t i( 0UL );
1094 
1095  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
1096  {
1097  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
1098  size_t j( SYM || HERM || UPP ? i : 0UL );
1099 
1100  for( ; (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
1101  {
1102  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1103  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1104  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1105  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1106  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+4UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
1107  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+4UL ) : K ) );
1108 
1109  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1110  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1111 
1112  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
1113  size_t k( kbegin );
1114 
1115  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1116  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
1117  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
1118  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
1119  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
1120  const SIMDType b3( B.load(k,j+2UL) );
1121  const SIMDType b4( B.load(k,j+3UL) );
1122  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
1123  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
1124  xmm3 += a1 * b3;
1125  xmm4 += a1 * b4;
1126  xmm5 += a2 * b1;
1127  xmm6 += a2 * b2;
1128  xmm7 += a2 * b3;
1129  xmm8 += a2 * b4;
1130  }
1131 
1132  (~C)(i ,j ) = sum( xmm1 );
1133  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 );
1134  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) = sum( xmm3 );
1135  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) = sum( xmm4 );
1136  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) = sum( xmm5 );
1137  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm6 );
1138  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) = sum( xmm7 );
1139  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) = sum( xmm8 );
1140 
1141  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1142  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
1143  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1144  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
1145  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
1146  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
1147  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1148  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
1149  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
1150  }
1151  }
1152 
1153  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
1154  {
1155  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1156  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1157  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1158  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1159  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
1160  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
1161 
1162  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1163  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1164 
1165  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
1166  size_t k( kbegin );
1167 
1168  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1169  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
1170  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
1171  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
1172  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
1173  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
1174  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
1175  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
1176  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
1177  }
1178 
1179  (~C)(i ,j ) = sum( xmm1 );
1180  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 );
1181  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) = sum( xmm3 );
1182  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm4 );
1183 
1184  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1185  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
1186  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1187  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
1188  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1189  }
1190  }
1191 
1192  if( j < jend )
1193  {
1194  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1195  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1196  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1197  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
1198 
1199  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1200  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1201 
1202  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
1203  size_t k( kbegin );
1204 
1205  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1206  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
1207  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
1208  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
1209  }
1210 
1211  (~C)(i ,j) = sum( xmm1 );
1212  (~C)(i+1UL,j) = sum( xmm2 );
1213 
1214  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1215  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
1216  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
1217  }
1218  }
1219  }
1220 
1221  for( ; i<M; ++i )
1222  {
1223  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
1224  size_t j( SYM || HERM || UPP ? i : 0UL );
1225 
1226  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
1227  {
1228  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1229  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1230  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1231  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+4UL ):( K ) );
1232 
1233  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1234  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1235 
1236  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
1237  size_t k( kbegin );
1238 
1239  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1240  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
1241  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
1242  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
1243  xmm3 += a1 * B.load(k,j+2UL);
1244  xmm4 += a1 * B.load(k,j+3UL);
1245  }
1246 
1247  (~C)(i,j ) = sum( xmm1 );
1248  (~C)(i,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 );
1249  (~C)(i,j+2UL) = sum( xmm3 );
1250  (~C)(i,j+3UL) = sum( xmm4 );
1251 
1252  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1253  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
1254  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1255  (~C)(i,j+2UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
1256  (~C)(i,j+3UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
1257  }
1258  }
1259 
1260  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
1261  {
1262  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1263  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1264  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1265  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
1266 
1267  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1268  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1269 
1270  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
1271  size_t k( kbegin );
1272 
1273  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1274  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
1275  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
1276  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
1277  }
1278 
1279  (~C)(i,j ) = sum( xmm1 );
1280  (~C)(i,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 );
1281 
1282  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1283  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
1284  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1285  }
1286  }
1287 
1288  for( ; j<jend; ++j )
1289  {
1290  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1291  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1292  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1293 
1294  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
1295  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1296 
1297  SIMDType xmm1;
1298  size_t k( kbegin );
1299 
1300  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1301  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
1302  }
1303 
1304  (~C)(i,j) = sum( xmm1 );
1305 
1306  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
1307  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
1308  }
1309  }
1310  }
1311  }
1312 
1313  if( SYM || HERM ) {
1314  for( size_t i=2UL; i<M; ++i ) {
1315  const size_t jend( 2UL * ( i/2UL ) );
1316  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jend; ++j ) {
1317  (~C)(i,j) = HERM ? conj( (~C)(j,i) ) : (~C)(j,i);
1318  }
1319  }
1320  }
1321  else if( LOW && !UPP ) {
1322  for( size_t j=2UL; j<N; ++j ) {
1323  const size_t iend( 2UL * ( j/2UL ) );
1324  for( size_t i=0UL; i<iend; ++i ) {
1325  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
1326  }
1327  }
1328  }
1329  else if( !LOW && UPP ) {
1330  for( size_t i=2UL; i<M; ++i ) {
1331  const size_t jend( 2UL * ( i/2UL ) );
1332  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jend; ++j ) {
1333  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
1334  }
1335  }
1336  }
1337  }
1339  //**********************************************************************************************
1340 
1341  //**Vectorized default assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)***************
1356  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1357  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1358  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1359  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1360  selectSmallAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1361  {
1362  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
1363 
1364  const size_t M( A.rows() );
1365  const size_t N( B.columns() );
1366  const size_t K( A.columns() );
1367 
1368  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
1369 
1370  if( LOW && UPP ) {
1371  reset( ~C );
1372  }
1373 
1374  {
1375  size_t i( 0UL );
1376 
1377  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (i+4UL) <= M; i+=4UL )
1378  {
1379  const size_t jend( SYM || HERM || LOW ? i+4UL : N );
1380  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
1381 
1382  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
1383  {
1384  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1385  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1386  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1387  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1388  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+4UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+4UL ) )
1389  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
1390 
1391  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1392  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1393 
1394  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
1395  size_t k( kbegin );
1396 
1397  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1398  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
1399  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
1400  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+2UL,k) );
1401  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+3UL,k) );
1402  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
1403  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
1404  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
1405  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
1406  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
1407  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
1408  xmm5 += a3 * b1;
1409  xmm6 += a3 * b2;
1410  xmm7 += a4 * b1;
1411  xmm8 += a4 * b2;
1412  }
1413 
1414  (~C)(i ,j ) = sum( xmm1 );
1415  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 );
1416  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) = sum( xmm3 );
1417  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm4 );
1418  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) = sum( xmm5 );
1419  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm6 );
1420  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) = sum( xmm7 );
1421  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm8 );
1422 
1423  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1424  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
1425  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1426  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
1427  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1428  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j );
1429  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1430  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j );
1431  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1432  }
1433  }
1434 
1435  if( j < jend )
1436  {
1437  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1438  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1439  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1440  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+4UL ):( K ) );
1441 
1442  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1443  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1444 
1445  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
1446  size_t k( kbegin );
1447 
1448  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1449  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
1450  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
1451  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
1452  xmm3 += A.load(i+2UL,k) * b1;
1453  xmm4 += A.load(i+3UL,k) * b1;
1454  }
1455 
1456  (~C)(i ,j) = sum( xmm1 );
1457  (~C)(i+1UL,j) = sum( xmm2 );
1458  (~C)(i+2UL,j) = sum( xmm3 );
1459  (~C)(i+3UL,j) = sum( xmm4 );
1460 
1461  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1462  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
1463  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
1464  (~C)(i+2UL,j) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j);
1465  (~C)(i+3UL,j) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j);
1466  }
1467  }
1468  }
1469 
1470  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
1471  {
1472  size_t j( 0UL );
1473 
1474  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
1475  {
1476  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1477  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1478  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1479  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1480  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
1481  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
1482 
1483  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1484  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1485 
1486  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
1487  size_t k( kbegin );
1488 
1489  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1490  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
1491  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
1492  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
1493  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
1494  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
1495  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
1496  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
1497  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
1498  }
1499 
1500  (~C)(i ,j ) = sum( xmm1 );
1501  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 );
1502  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) = sum( xmm3 );
1503  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm4 );
1504 
1505  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1506  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
1507  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1508  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
1509  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1510  }
1511  }
1512 
1513  if( j < N )
1514  {
1515  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1516  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1517  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1518  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
1519 
1520  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1521  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1522 
1523  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
1524  size_t k( kbegin );
1525 
1526  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1527  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
1528  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
1529  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
1530  }
1531 
1532  (~C)(i ,j) = sum( xmm1 );
1533  (~C)(i+1UL,j) = sum( xmm2 );
1534 
1535  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1536  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
1537  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
1538  }
1539  }
1540  }
1541 
1542  for( ; i<M; ++i )
1543  {
1544  const size_t jend( LOW && UPP ? i+1UL : N );
1545  size_t j( LOW && UPP ? i : 0UL );
1546 
1547  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
1548  {
1549  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1550  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1551  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1552  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
1553 
1554  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
1555  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1556 
1557  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
1558  size_t k( kbegin );
1559 
1560  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1561  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
1562  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
1563  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
1564  }
1565 
1566  (~C)(i,j ) = sum( xmm1 );
1567  (~C)(i,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 );
1568 
1569  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
1570  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
1571  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1572  }
1573  }
1574 
1575  for( ; j<jend; ++j )
1576  {
1577  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1578  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
1579  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
1580 
1581  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
1582  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1583 
1584  SIMDType xmm1;
1585  size_t k( kbegin );
1586 
1587  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
1588  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
1589  }
1590 
1591  (~C)(i,j) = sum( xmm1 );
1592 
1593  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
1594  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
1595  }
1596  }
1597  }
1598  }
1599 
1600  if( ( SYM || HERM ) && ( N > 4UL ) ) {
1601  for( size_t j=4UL; j<N; ++j ) {
1602  const size_t iend( 4UL * ( j/4UL ) );
1603  for( size_t i=0UL; i<iend; ++i ) {
1604  (~C)(i,j) = HERM ? conj( (~C)(j,i) ) : (~C)(j,i);
1605  }
1606  }
1607  }
1608  else if( LOW && !UPP ) {
1609  for( size_t j=4UL; j<N; ++j ) {
1610  const size_t iend( 4UL * ( j/4UL ) );
1611  for( size_t i=0UL; i<iend; ++i ) {
1612  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
1613  }
1614  }
1615  }
1616  else if( !LOW && UPP ) {
1617  for( size_t i=4UL; i<N; ++i ) {
1618  const size_t jend( 4UL * ( i/4UL ) );
1619  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jend; ++j ) {
1620  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
1621  }
1622  }
1623  }
1624  }
1626  //**********************************************************************************************
1627 
1628  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)***************************************
1642  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1643  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1644  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1645  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1646  selectLargeAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1647  {
1648  selectDefaultAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1649  }
1651  //**********************************************************************************************
1652 
1653  //**Vectorized default assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)****************************
1668  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1669  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1670  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1671  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1672  selectLargeAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1673  {
1674  if( SYM )
1675  smmm( C, A, B, ElementType(1) );
1676  else if( HERM )
1677  hmmm( C, A, B, ElementType(1) );
1678  else if( LOW )
1679  lmmm( C, A, B, ElementType(1), ElementType(0) );
1680  else if( UPP )
1681  ummm( C, A, B, ElementType(1), ElementType(0) );
1682  else
1683  mmm( C, A, B, ElementType(1), ElementType(0) );
1684  }
1686  //**********************************************************************************************
1687 
1688  //**BLAS-based assignment to dense matrices (default)*******************************************
1702  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1703  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1704  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1705  static inline DisableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1706  selectBlasAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1707  {
1708  selectLargeAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1709  }
1711  //**********************************************************************************************
1712 
1713  //**BLAS-based assignment to dense matrices*****************************************************
1714 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
1715 
1728  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1729  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1730  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1731  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1732  selectBlasAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1733  {
1734  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
1735 
1736  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
1737  assign( C, B );
1738  trmm( C, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
1739  }
1740  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
1741  assign( C, A );
1742  trmm( C, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
1743  }
1744  else {
1745  gemm( C, A, B, ET(1), ET(0) );
1746  }
1747  }
1749 #endif
1750  //**********************************************************************************************
1751 
1752  //**Assignment to sparse matrices***************************************************************
1765  template< typename MT // Type of the target sparse matrix
1766  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target sparse matrix
1767  friend inline void assign( SparseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
1768  {
1769  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
1770 
1771  typedef IfTrue_< SO, OppositeType, ResultType > TmpType;
1772 
1773  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
1774  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
1775  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
1776  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
1777  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MATRICES_MUST_HAVE_SAME_STORAGE_ORDER( MT, TmpType );
1778  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_REFERENCE_TYPE( CompositeType_<TmpType> );
1779 
1780  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1781  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1782 
1783  const ForwardFunctor fwd;
1784 
1785  const TmpType tmp( serial( rhs ) );
1786  assign( ~lhs, fwd( tmp ) );
1787  }
1789  //**********************************************************************************************
1790 
1791  //**Addition assignment to dense matrices*******************************************************
1804  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
1805  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
1806  friend inline void addAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
1807  {
1808  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
1809 
1810  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1811  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1812 
1813  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
1814  return;
1815  }
1816 
1817  LT A( serial( rhs.lhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
1818  RT B( serial( rhs.rhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
1819 
1820  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1821  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1822  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1823  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1824  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1825  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
1826 
1827  DMatTDMatMultExpr::selectAddAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B );
1828  }
1830  //**********************************************************************************************
1831 
1832  //**Addition assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)************************************
1843  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1844  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1845  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1846  static inline void selectAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1847  {
1848  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value || IsDiagonal<MT5>::value ) ||
1849  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < DMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
1850  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1851  else
1852  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1853  }

1857  //**Default addition assignment to row-major dense matrices (general/general)*******************
1871  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1872  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1873  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1874  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
1875  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1876  {
1877  const size_t M( A.rows() );
1878  const size_t N( B.columns() );
1879  const size_t K( A.columns() );
1880 
1881  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
1882 
1883  const size_t ibegin( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
1884  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value && M > 1UL ) ? 2UL : 1UL )
1885  :( 0UL ) );
1886  const size_t iend( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
1887  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value && M > 1UL ) ? M-2UL : M-1UL )
1888  :( M ) );
1889  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
1890 
1891  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i )
1892  {
1893  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1894  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
1895  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+2UL : i+1UL )
1896  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
1897  :( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )
1898  ?( UPP ? max( i, 1UL ) : 1UL )
1899  :( UPP ? i : 0UL ) ) );
1900  const size_t jend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value )
1901  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
1902  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i-1UL : i )
1903  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
1904  :( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value )
1905  ?( LOW ? min(i+1UL,N-1UL) : N-1UL )
1906  :( LOW ? i+1UL : N ) ) );
1907 
1908  if( ( LOW || UPP ) && ( jbegin > jend ) ) continue;
1909  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
1910 
1911  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jend; ++j )
1912  {
1913  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1914  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1915  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
1916  , ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1917  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
1918  :( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1919  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
1920  :( 0UL ) ) );
1921  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1922  ?( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1923  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
1924  , ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
1925  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
1926  :( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1927  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
1928  :( K ) ) );
1929  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin < kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
1930 
1931  const size_t knum( kend - kbegin );
1932  const size_t kpos( kbegin + ( knum & size_t(-2) ) );
1933 
1934  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kpos; k+=2UL ) {
1935  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k ) * B(k ,j);
1936  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k+1UL) * B(k+1UL,j);
1937  }
1938  if( kpos < kend ) {
1939  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,kpos) * B(kpos,j);
1940  }
1941  }
1942  }
1943  }

1961  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1962  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1963  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1964  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
1965  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1966  {
1967  const size_t M( A.rows() );
1968  const size_t N( B.columns() );
1969  const size_t K( A.columns() );
1970 
1971  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
1972 
1973  const size_t jbegin( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )
1974  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value && N > 1UL ) ? 2UL : 1UL )
1975  :( 0UL ) );
1976  const size_t jend( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value )
1977  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value && N > 1UL ) ? N-2UL : N-1UL )
1978  :( N ) );
1979  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
1980 
1981  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jend; ++j )
1982  {
1983  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value )
1984  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
1985  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+2UL : j+1UL )
1986  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1987  :( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
1988  ?( LOW ? max( j, 1UL ) : 1UL )
1989  :( LOW ? j : 0UL ) ) );
1990  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1991  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
1992  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )?( j-1UL ):( j ) )
1993  :( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )?( j ):( j+1UL ) ) )

1996  :( UPP ? j+1UL : M ) ) );
1997 
1998  if( ( LOW || UPP ) && ( ibegin > iend ) ) continue;
1999  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
2000 
2001  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i )
2002  {
2003  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2004  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
2005  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
2006  , ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
2007  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
2008  :( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
2009  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
2010  :( 0UL ) ) );
2011  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2012  ?( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
2013  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
2014  , ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
2015  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
2016  :( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
2017  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
2018  :( K ) ) );
2019  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin < kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
2020 
2021  const size_t knum( kend - kbegin );
2022  const size_t kpos( kbegin + ( knum & size_t(-2) ) );
2023 
2024  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kpos; k+=2UL ) {
2025  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k ) * B(k ,j);
2026  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k+1UL) * B(k+1UL,j);
2027  }
2028  if( kpos < kend ) {
2029  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,kpos) * B(kpos,j);
2030  }
2031  }
2032  }
2033  }

2280 
2281  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)*********
2296  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2297  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2298  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2299  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2300  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2301  {
2302  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
2303 
2304  const size_t M( A.rows() );
2305  const size_t N( B.columns() );
2306  const size_t K( A.columns() );
2307 
2308  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
2309 
2310  size_t i( 0UL );
2311 
2312  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
2313  {
2314  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
2315  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
2316 
2317  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
2318  {
2319  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2320  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2321  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2322  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2323  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+4UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
2324  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+4UL ) : K ) );
2325 
2326  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2327  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2328 
2329  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
2330  size_t k( kbegin );
2331 
2332  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2333  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
2334  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
2335  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
2336  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
2337  const SIMDType b3( B.load(k,j+2UL) );
2338  const SIMDType b4( B.load(k,j+3UL) );
2339  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
2340  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
2341  xmm3 += a1 * b3;
2342  xmm4 += a1 * b4;
2343  xmm5 += a2 * b1;
2344  xmm6 += a2 * b2;
2345  xmm7 += a2 * b3;
2346  xmm8 += a2 * b4;
2347  }
2348 
2349  (~C)(i ,j ) += sum( xmm1 );
2350  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 );
2351  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) += sum( xmm3 );
2352  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) += sum( xmm4 );
2353  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += sum( xmm5 );
2354  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm6 );
2355  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) += sum( xmm7 );
2356  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) += sum( xmm8 );
2357 
2358  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2359  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
2360  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2361  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
2362  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
2363  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
2364  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2365  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
2366  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
2367  }
2368  }
2369 
2370  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
2371  {
2372  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2373  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2374  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2375  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2376  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
2377  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
2378 
2379  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2380  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2381 
2382  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
2383  size_t k( kbegin );
2384 
2385  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2386  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
2387  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
2388  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
2389  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
2390  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
2391  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
2392  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
2393  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
2394  }
2395 
2396  (~C)(i ,j ) += sum( xmm1 );
2397  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 );
2398  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += sum( xmm3 );
2399  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm4 );
2400 
2401  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2402  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
2403  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2404  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
2405  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2406  }
2407  }
2408 
2409  if( j < jend )
2410  {
2411  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2412  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2413  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2414  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
2415 
2416  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2417  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2418 
2419  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
2420  size_t k( kbegin );
2421 
2422  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2423  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
2424  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
2425  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
2426  }
2427 
2428  (~C)(i ,j) += sum( xmm1 );
2429  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += sum( xmm2 );
2430 
2431  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2432  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
2433  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
2434  }
2435  }
2436  }
2437 
2438  if( i < M )
2439  {
2440  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
2441  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
2442 
2443  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
2444  {
2445  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2446  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2447  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2448  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+4UL ):( K ) );
2449 
2450  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2451  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2452 
2453  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
2454  size_t k( kbegin );
2455 
2456  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2457  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
2458  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
2459  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
2460  xmm3 += a1 * B.load(k,j+2UL);
2461  xmm4 += a1 * B.load(k,j+3UL);
2462  }
2463 
2464  (~C)(i,j ) += sum( xmm1 );
2465  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 );
2466  (~C)(i,j+2UL) += sum( xmm3 );
2467  (~C)(i,j+3UL) += sum( xmm4 );
2468 
2469  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2470  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
2471  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2472  (~C)(i,j+2UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
2473  (~C)(i,j+3UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
2474  }
2475  }
2476 
2477  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
2478  {
2479  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2480  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2481  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2482  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
2483 
2484  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2485  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2486 
2487  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
2488  size_t k( kbegin );
2489 
2490  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2491  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
2492  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
2493  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
2494  }
2495 
2496  (~C)(i,j ) += sum( xmm1 );
2497  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 );
2498 
2499  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2500  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
2501  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2502  }
2503  }
2504 
2505  if( j < jend )
2506  {
2507  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2508  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2509  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2510 
2511  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
2512  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2513 
2514  SIMDType xmm1;
2515  size_t k( kbegin );
2516 
2517  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2518  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
2519  }
2520 
2521  (~C)(i,j) += sum( xmm1 );
2522 
2523  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
2524  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
2525  }
2526  }
2527  }
2528  }
2530  //**********************************************************************************************
2531 
2532  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)******
2547  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2548  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2549  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2550  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2551  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2552  {
2553  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
2554 
2555  const size_t M( A.rows() );
2556  const size_t N( B.columns() );
2557  const size_t K( A.columns() );
2558 
2559  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
2560 
2561  size_t i( 0UL );
2562 
2563  for( ; !LOW && !UPP && (i+4UL) <= M; i+=4UL )
2564  {
2565  size_t j( 0UL );
2566 
2567  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
2568  {
2569  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2570  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2571  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2572  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2573  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+4UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+4UL ) )
2574  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
2575 
2576  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2577  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2578 
2579  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
2580  size_t k( kbegin );
2581 
2582  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2583  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
2584  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
2585  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+2UL,k) );
2586  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+3UL,k) );
2587  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
2588  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
2589  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
2590  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
2591  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
2592  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
2593  xmm5 += a3 * b1;
2594  xmm6 += a3 * b2;
2595  xmm7 += a4 * b1;
2596  xmm8 += a4 * b2;
2597  }
2598 
2599  (~C)(i ,j ) += sum( xmm1 );
2600  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 );
2601  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += sum( xmm3 );
2602  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm4 );
2603  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) += sum( xmm5 );
2604  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm6 );
2605  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) += sum( xmm7 );
2606  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm8 );
2607 
2608  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2609  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
2610  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2611  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
2612  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2613  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j );
2614  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2615  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j );
2616  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2617  }
2618  }
2619 
2620  if( j < N )
2621  {
2622  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2623  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2624  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2625  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+4UL ):( K ) );
2626 
2627  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2628  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2629 
2630  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
2631  size_t k( kbegin );
2632 
2633  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2634  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
2635  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
2636  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
2637  xmm3 += A.load(i+2UL,k) * b1;
2638  xmm4 += A.load(i+3UL,k) * b1;
2639  }
2640 
2641  (~C)(i ,j) += sum( xmm1 );
2642  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += sum( xmm2 );
2643  (~C)(i+2UL,j) += sum( xmm3 );
2644  (~C)(i+3UL,j) += sum( xmm4 );
2645 
2646  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2647  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
2648  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
2649  (~C)(i+2UL,j) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j);
2650  (~C)(i+3UL,j) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j);
2651  }
2652  }
2653  }
2654 
2655  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
2656  {
2657  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
2658  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
2659 
2660  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
2661  {
2662  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2663  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2664  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2665  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2666  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
2667  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
2668 
2669  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2670  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2671 
2672  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
2673  size_t k( kbegin );
2674 
2675  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2676  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
2677  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
2678  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
2679  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
2680  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
2681  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
2682  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
2683  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
2684  }
2685 
2686  (~C)(i ,j ) += sum( xmm1 );
2687  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 );
2688  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += sum( xmm3 );
2689  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm4 );
2690 
2691  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2692  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
2693  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2694  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
2695  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2696  }
2697  }
2698 
2699  if( j < jend )
2700  {
2701  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2702  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2703  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2704  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
2705 
2706  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2707  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2708 
2709  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
2710  size_t k( kbegin );
2711 
2712  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2713  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
2714  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
2715  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
2716  }
2717 
2718  (~C)(i ,j) += sum( xmm1 );
2719  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += sum( xmm2 );
2720 
2721  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2722  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
2723  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
2724  }
2725  }
2726  }
2727 
2728  if( i < M )
2729  {
2730  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
2731  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
2732 
2733  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
2734  {
2735  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2736  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2737  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2738  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
2739 
2740  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
2741  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2742 
2743  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
2744  size_t k( kbegin );
2745 
2746  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2747  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
2748  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
2749  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
2750  }
2751 
2752  (~C)(i,j ) += sum( xmm1 );
2753  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 );
2754 
2755  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
2756  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
2757  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
2758  }
2759  }
2760 
2761  if( j < jend )
2762  {
2763  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2764  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
2765  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
2766 
2767  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
2768  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2769 
2770  SIMDType xmm1;
2771  size_t k( kbegin );
2772 
2773  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
2774  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
2775  }
2776 
2777  (~C)(i,j) += sum( xmm1 );
2778 
2779  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
2780  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
2781  }
2782  }
2783  }
2784  }

2805  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2806  selectLargeAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2807  {

2813  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)*******************
2828  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2829  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2830  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2831  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2832  selectLargeAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2833  {
2834  if( LOW )
2835  lmmm( C, A, B, ElementType(1), ElementType(1) );
2836  else if( UPP )
2837  ummm( C, A, B, ElementType(1), ElementType(1) );
2838  else
2839  mmm( C, A, B, ElementType(1), ElementType(1) );
2840  }

2861  static inline DisableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2862  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2863  {

2865  }

2869  //**BLAS-based addition assignment to dense matrices********************************************
2870 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
2871 
2884  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2885  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2886  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2887  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2888  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2889  {
2890  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
2891 
2892  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
2893  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( B ) );
2894  trmm( tmp, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
2895  addAssign( C, tmp );
2896  }
2897  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
2898  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( A ) );
2899  trmm( tmp, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
2900  addAssign( C, tmp );
2901  }
2902  else {
2903  gemm( C, A, B, ET(1), ET(1) );
2904  }
2905  }
2907 #endif

2914  //**Subtraction assignment to dense matrices****************************************************
2927  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
2928  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
2929  friend inline void subAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
2930  {
2931  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
2932 
2933  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2934  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
2935 
2936  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
2937  return;
2938  }
2939 
2940  LT A( serial( rhs.lhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
2941  RT B( serial( rhs.rhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
2942 
2943  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2944  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
2945  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2946  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
2947  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2948  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
2949 
2950  DMatTDMatMultExpr::selectSubAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B );
2951  }
2953  //**********************************************************************************************
2954 
2955  //**Subtraction assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)*********************************
2966  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2967  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2968  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2969  static inline void selectSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2970  {
2971  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value || IsDiagonal<MT5>::value ) ||
2972  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < DMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
2973  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( C, A, B );
2974  else
2975  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( C, A, B );
2976  }

2980  //**Default subtraction assignment to row-major dense matrices (general/general)****************
2994  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix

3422  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
3423  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
3424  {
3425  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
3426 
3427  const size_t M( A.rows() );
3428  const size_t N( B.columns() );
3429  const size_t K( A.columns() );
3430 
3431  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
3432 
3433  size_t i( 0UL );
3434 
3435  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
3436  {
3437  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
3438  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
3439 
3440  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
3441  {
3442  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3443  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3444  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3445  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )

3447  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+4UL ) : K ) );

3450  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3451 
3452  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
3453  size_t k( kbegin );

3456  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
3457  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
3458  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
3459  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
3460  const SIMDType b3( B.load(k,j+2UL) );
3461  const SIMDType b4( B.load(k,j+3UL) );
3462  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
3463  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
3464  xmm3 += a1 * b3;
3465  xmm4 += a1 * b4;
3466  xmm5 += a2 * b1;
3467  xmm6 += a2 * b2;
3468  xmm7 += a2 * b3;
3469  xmm8 += a2 * b4;

3473  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 );
3474  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) -= sum( xmm3 );
3475  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) -= sum( xmm4 );

3477  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm6 );
3478  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) -= sum( xmm7 );
3479  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) -= sum( xmm8 );

3482  (~C)(i ,j ) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
3483  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3484  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
3485  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
3486  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
3487  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3488  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
3489  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
3490  }

3499  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
3500  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );

3503  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );

3511  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
3512  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
3513  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
3514  xmm2 += a1 * b2;

3516  xmm4 += a2 * b2;

3526  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3527  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
3528  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3529  }
3530  }

3533  {
3534  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3535  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3536  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );

3548  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
