3552  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= sum( xmm2 );
3553 
3554  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
3555  (~C)(i ,j) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
3556  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
3557  }
3558  }
3559  }
3560 
3561  if( i < M )
3562  {
3563  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
3564  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
3565 
3566  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
3567  {
3568  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3569  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3570  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3571  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+4UL ):( K ) );
3572 
3573  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
3574  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3575 
3576  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
3577  size_t k( kbegin );
3578 
3579  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3580  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
3581  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
3582  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
3583  xmm3 += a1 * B.load(k,j+2UL);
3584  xmm4 += a1 * B.load(k,j+3UL);
3585  }
3586 
3587  (~C)(i,j ) -= sum( xmm1 );
3588  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 );
3589  (~C)(i,j+2UL) -= sum( xmm3 );
3590  (~C)(i,j+3UL) -= sum( xmm4 );
3591 
3592  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
3593  (~C)(i,j ) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j );
3594  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3595  (~C)(i,j+2UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+2UL);
3596  (~C)(i,j+3UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+3UL);
3597  }
3598  }
3599 
3600  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
3601  {
3602  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3603  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3604  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3605  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
3606 
3607  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
3608  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3609 
3610  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
3611  size_t k( kbegin );
3612 
3613  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3614  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
3615  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
3616  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
3617  }
3618 
3619  (~C)(i,j ) -= sum( xmm1 );
3620  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 );
3621 
3622  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
3623  (~C)(i,j ) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j );
3624  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3625  }
3626  }
3627 
3628  if( j < jend )
3629  {
3630  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3631  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3632  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3633 
3634  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
3635  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3636 
3637  SIMDType xmm1;
3638  size_t k( kbegin );
3639 
3640  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3641  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
3642  }
3643 
3644  (~C)(i,j) -= sum( xmm1 );
3645 
3646  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
3647  (~C)(i,j) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j);
3648  }
3649  }
3650  }
3651  }
3653  //**********************************************************************************************
3654 
3655  //**Default subtraction assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)**************
3670  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
3671  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
3672  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
3673  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
3674  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
3675  {
3676  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
3677 
3678  const size_t M( A.rows() );
3679  const size_t N( B.columns() );
3680  const size_t K( A.columns() );
3681 
3682  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
3683 
3684  size_t i( 0UL );
3685 
3686  for( ; !LOW && !UPP && (i+4UL) <= M; i+=4UL )
3687  {
3688  size_t j( 0UL );
3689 
3690  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
3691  {
3692  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3693  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3694  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3695  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
3696  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+4UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+4UL ) )
3697  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
3698 
3699  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
3700  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3701 
3702  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
3703  size_t k( kbegin );
3704 
3705  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3706  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
3707  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
3708  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+2UL,k) );
3709  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+3UL,k) );
3710  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
3711  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
3712  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
3713  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
3714  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
3715  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
3716  xmm5 += a3 * b1;
3717  xmm6 += a3 * b2;
3718  xmm7 += a4 * b1;
3719  xmm8 += a4 * b2;
3720  }
3721 
3722  (~C)(i ,j ) -= sum( xmm1 );
3723  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 );
3724  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= sum( xmm3 );
3725  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm4 );
3726  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) -= sum( xmm5 );
3727  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm6 );
3728  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) -= sum( xmm7 );
3729  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm8 );
3730 
3731  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
3732  (~C)(i ,j ) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
3733  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3734  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
3735  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3736  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) -= A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j );
3737  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3738  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) -= A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j );
3739  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3740  }
3741  }
3742 
3743  if( j < N )
3744  {
3745  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3746  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3747  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3748  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+4UL ):( K ) );
3749 
3750  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
3751  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3752 
3753  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
3754  size_t k( kbegin );
3755 
3756  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3757  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
3758  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
3759  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
3760  xmm3 += A.load(i+2UL,k) * b1;
3761  xmm4 += A.load(i+3UL,k) * b1;
3762  }
3763 
3764  (~C)(i ,j) -= sum( xmm1 );
3765  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= sum( xmm2 );
3766  (~C)(i+2UL,j) -= sum( xmm3 );
3767  (~C)(i+3UL,j) -= sum( xmm4 );
3768 
3769  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
3770  (~C)(i ,j ) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
3771  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
3772  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) -= A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j );
3773  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) -= A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j );
3774  }
3775  }
3776  }
3777 
3778  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
3779  {
3780  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
3781  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
3782 
3783  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
3784  {
3785  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3786  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3787  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3788  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
3789  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
3790  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
3791 
3792  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
3793  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3794 
3795  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
3796  size_t k( kbegin );
3797 
3798  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3799  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
3800  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
3801  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
3802  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
3803  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
3804  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
3805  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
3806  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
3807  }
3808 
3809  (~C)(i ,j ) -= sum( xmm1 );
3810  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 );
3811  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= sum( xmm3 );
3812  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm4 );
3813 
3814  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
3815  (~C)(i ,j ) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j );
3816  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3817  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j );
3818  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3819  }
3820  }
3821 
3822  if( j < jend )
3823  {
3824  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3825  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3826  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3827  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
3828 
3829  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
3830  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3831 
3832  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
3833  size_t k( kbegin );
3834 
3835  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3836  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
3837  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
3838  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
3839  }
3840 
3841  (~C)(i ,j) -= sum( xmm1 );
3842  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= sum( xmm2 );
3843 
3844  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
3845  (~C)(i ,j) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
3846  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
3847  }
3848  }
3849  }
3850 
3851  if( i < M )
3852  {
3853  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
3854  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
3855 
3856  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
3857  {
3858  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3859  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3860  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3861  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
3862 
3863  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
3864  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3865 
3866  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
3867  size_t k( kbegin );
3868 
3869  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3870  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
3871  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
3872  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
3873  }
3874 
3875  (~C)(i,j ) -= sum( xmm1 );
3876  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 );
3877 
3878  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
3879  (~C)(i,j ) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j );
3880  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3881  }
3882  }
3883 
3884  if( j < jend )
3885  {
3886  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3887  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
3888  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
3889 
3890  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
3891  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
3892 
3893  SIMDType xmm1;
3894  size_t k( kbegin );
3895 
3896  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
3897  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
3898  }
3899 
3900  (~C)(i,j) -= sum( xmm1 );
3901 
3902  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
3903  (~C)(i,j) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j);
3904  }
3905  }
3906  }
3907  }

3911  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)***************************
3925  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
3926  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
3927  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
3928  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
3929  selectLargeSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
3930  {
3931  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( ~C, A, B );
3932  }
3934  //**********************************************************************************************
3935 
3936  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)***************************
3951  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
3952  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
3953  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
3954  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
3955  selectLargeSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
3956  {
3957  if( LOW )
3958  lmmm( C, A, B, ElementType(-1), ElementType(1) );
3959  else if( UPP )
3960  ummm( C, A, B, ElementType(-1), ElementType(1) );
3961  else
3962  mmm( C, A, B, ElementType(-1), ElementType(1) );
3963  }

3967  //**BLAS-based subtraction assignment to dense matrices (default)*******************************
3981  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
3982  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
3983  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
3984  static inline DisableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
3985  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
3986  {
3987  selectLargeSubAssignKernel( C, A, B );
3988  }
3990  //**********************************************************************************************
3991 
3992  //**BLAS-based subraction assignment to dense matrices******************************************
3993 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
3994 
4007  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4008  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4009  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4010  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
4011  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
4012  {
4013  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
4014 
4015  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
4016  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( B ) );
4017  trmm( tmp, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
4018  subAssign( C, tmp );
4019  }
4020  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
4021  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( A ) );
4022  trmm( tmp, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
4023  subAssign( C, tmp );
4024  }
4025  else {
4026  gemm( C, A, B, ET(-1), ET(1) );
4027  }
4028  }
4030 #endif

4033  //**Subtraction assignment to sparse matrices***************************************************
4034  // No special implementation for the subtraction assignment to sparse matrices.
4035  //**********************************************************************************************
4036 
4037  //**Multiplication assignment to dense matrices*************************************************
4038  // No special implementation for the multiplication assignment to dense matrices.
4039  //**********************************************************************************************
4040 
4041  //**Multiplication assignment to sparse matrices************************************************
4042  // No special implementation for the multiplication assignment to sparse matrices.
4043  //**********************************************************************************************
4044 
4045  //**SMP assignment to dense matrices************************************************************
4060  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
4061  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
4062  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
4063  smpAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
4064  {
4065  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
4066 
4067  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4068  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4069 
4070  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL ) {
4071  return;
4072  }
4073  else if( rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
4074  reset( ~lhs );
4075  return;
4076  }
4077 
4078  LT A( rhs.lhs_ ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
4079  RT B( rhs.rhs_ ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
4080 
4081  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4082  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4083  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4084  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4085  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4086  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
4087 
4088  smpAssign( ~lhs, A * B );
4089  }

4092 
4093  //**SMP assignment to sparse matrices***********************************************************
4108  template< typename MT // Type of the target sparse matrix
4109  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target sparse matrix
4110  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
4111  smpAssign( SparseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
4112  {
4113  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
4114 
4115  typedef IfTrue_< SO, OppositeType, ResultType > TmpType;
4116 
4117  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
4118  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
4119  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
4120  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
4121  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MATRICES_MUST_HAVE_SAME_STORAGE_ORDER( MT, TmpType );
4122  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_REFERENCE_TYPE( CompositeType_<TmpType> );
4123 
4124  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4125  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4126 
4127  const ForwardFunctor fwd;
4128 
4129  const TmpType tmp( rhs );
4130  smpAssign( ~lhs, fwd( tmp ) );
4131  }
4133  //**********************************************************************************************
4134 
4135  //**SMP addition assignment to dense matrices***************************************************
4151  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
4152  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
4153  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
4154  smpAddAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
4155  {
4156  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
4157 
4158  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4159  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4160 
4161  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
4162  return;
4163  }
4164 
4165  LT A( rhs.lhs_ ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
4166  RT B( rhs.rhs_ ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
4167 
4168  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4169  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4170  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4171  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4172  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4173  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
4174 
4175  smpAddAssign( ~lhs, A * B );
4176  }

4210  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {

4223

4225  }

4563  //**Assignment to dense matrices****************************************************************
4575  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
4576  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
4577  friend inline void assign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
4578  {
4579  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
4580 
4581  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4582  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4583 
4584  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
4585  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
4586 
4587  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL ) {
4588  return;
4589  }
4590  else if( left.columns() == 0UL ) {
4591  reset( ~lhs );
4592  return;
4593  }
4594 
4595  LT A( serial( left ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
4596  RT B( serial( right ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
4597 
4598  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4599  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
4600  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4601  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
4602  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4603  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4604 
4605  DMatScalarMultExpr::selectAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B, rhs.scalar_ );
4606  }

4609  //**Assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)*********************************************
4620  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4621  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4622  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4623  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4624  static inline void selectAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4625  {
4626  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value || IsDiagonal<MT5>::value ) ||
4627  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < DMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
4628  selectSmallAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
4629  else
4630  selectBlasAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
4631  }
4632  //**********************************************************************************************
4633 
4634  //**Default assignment to row-major dense matrices (general/general)****************************
4648  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4649  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4650  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4651  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4652  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
4653  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4654  {
4655  const size_t M( A.rows() );
4656  const size_t N( B.columns() );
4657  const size_t K( A.columns() );
4658 
4659  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
4660 
4661  const size_t ibegin( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
4662  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value && M > 1UL ) ? 2UL : 1UL )
4663  :( 0UL ) );
4664  const size_t iend( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
4665  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value && M > 1UL ) ? M-2UL : M-1UL )
4666  :( M ) );
4667  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4668 
4669  for( size_t i=0UL; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
4670  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j ) {
4671  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4672  }
4673  }
4674  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i )
4675  {
4676  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4677  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
4678  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+2UL : i+1UL )
4679  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
4680  :( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )
4681  ?( SYM || HERM || UPP ? max( i, 1UL ) : 1UL )
4682  :( SYM || HERM || UPP ? i : 0UL ) ) );
4683  const size_t jend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value )
4684  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
4685  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i-1UL : i )
4686  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
4687  :( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value )
4688  ?( LOW ? min(i+1UL,N-1UL) : N-1UL )
4689  :( LOW ? i+1UL : N ) ) );
4690 
4691  if( ( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) && ( jbegin > jend ) ) {
4692  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j ) {
4693  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4694  }
4695  continue;
4696  }
4697 
4698  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4699 
4700  for( size_t j=( SYM || HERM ? i : 0UL ); j<jbegin; ++j ) {
4701  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4702  }
4703  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jend; ++j )
4704  {
4705  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4706  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
4707  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
4708  , ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
4709  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
4710  :( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
4711  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
4712  :( 0UL ) ) );
4713  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4714  ?( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4715  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
4716  , ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
4717  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
4718  :( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4719  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
4720  :( K ) ) );
4721  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin < kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4722 
4723  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,kbegin) * B(kbegin,j);
4724  for( size_t k=kbegin+1UL; k<kend; ++k ) {
4725  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
4726  }
4727  (~C)(i,j) *= scalar;
4728  }
4729  for( size_t j=jend; j<N; ++j ) {
4730  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4731  }
4732  }
4733  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
4734  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j ) {
4735  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4736  }
4737  }
4738 
4739  if( SYM || HERM ) {
4740  for( size_t i=1UL; i<M; ++i ) {
4741  for( size_t j=0UL; j<i; ++j ) {
4742  (~C)(i,j) = HERM ? conj( (~C)(j,i) ) : (~C)(j,i);
4743  }
4744  }
4745  }
4746  }
4747  //**********************************************************************************************
4748 
4749  //**Default assignment to column-major dense matrices (general/general)*************************
4763  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4764  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4765  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4766  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4767  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
4768  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4769  {
4770  const size_t M( A.rows() );
4771  const size_t N( B.columns() );
4772  const size_t K( A.columns() );
4773 
4774  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
4775 
4776  const size_t jbegin( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )
4777  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value && N > 1UL ) ? 2UL : 1UL )
4778  :( 0UL ) );
4779  const size_t jend( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value )
4780  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value && N > 1UL ) ? N-2UL : N-1UL )
4781  :( N ) );
4782  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4783 
4784  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jbegin; ++j ) {
4785  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i ) {
4786  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4787  }
4788  }
4789  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jend; ++j )
4790  {
4791  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value )
4792  ?( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
4793  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+2UL : j+1UL )
4794  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
4795  :( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value )
4796  ?( SYM || HERM || LOW ? max( j, 1UL ) : 1UL )
4797  :( SYM || HERM || LOW ? j : 0UL ) ) );
4798  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4799  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
4800  ?( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )?( j-1UL ):( j ) )
4801  :( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value )?( j ):( j+1UL ) ) )
4802  :( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value )
4803  ?( UPP ? min(j+1UL,M-1UL) : M-1UL )
4804  :( UPP ? j+1UL : M ) ) );
4805 
4806  if( ( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) && ( ibegin > iend ) ) {
4807  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i ) {
4808  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4809  }
4810  continue;
4811  }
4812 
4813  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4814 
4815  for( size_t i=( SYM || HERM ? j : 0UL ); i<ibegin; ++i ) {
4816  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4817  }
4818  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i )
4819  {
4820  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4821  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
4822  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
4823  , ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
4824  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
4825  :( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
4826  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
4827  :( 0UL ) ) );
4828  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4829  ?( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4830  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
4831  , ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
4832  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
4833  :( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4834  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
4835  :( K ) ) );
4836  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin < kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4837 
4838  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,kbegin) * B(kbegin,j);
4839  for( size_t k=kbegin+1UL; k<kend; ++k ) {
4840  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
4841  }
4842  (~C)(i,j) *= scalar;
4843  }
4844  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
4845  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4846  }
4847  }
4848  for( size_t j=jend; j<N; ++j ) {
4849  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i ) {
4850  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4851  }
4852  }
4853 
4854  if( SYM || HERM ) {
4855  for( size_t j=1UL; j<N; ++j ) {
4856  for( size_t i=0UL; i<j; ++i ) {
4857  (~C)(i,j) = HERM ? conj( (~C)(j,i) ) : (~C)(j,i);
4858  }
4859  }
4860  }
4861  }
4862  //**********************************************************************************************
4863 
4864  //**Default assignment to row-major dense matrices (general/diagonal)***************************
4878  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4879  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4880  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4881  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4882  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
4883  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4884  {
4885  const size_t M( A.rows() );
4886  const size_t N( B.columns() );
4887 
4888  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i )
4889  {
4890  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4891  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
4892  :( 0UL ) );
4893  const size_t jend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4894  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
4895  :( N ) );
4896  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4897 
4898  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
4899  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jbegin; ++j ) {
4900  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4901  }
4902  }
4903  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jend; ++j ) {
4904  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
4905  }
4906  if( IsLower<MT4>::value ) {
4907  for( size_t j=jend; j<N; ++j ) {
4908  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4909  }
4910  }
4911  }
4912  }

4915  //**Default assignment to column-major dense matrices (general/diagonal)************************
4929  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4930  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4931  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4932  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4933  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
4934  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4935  {
4936  constexpr size_t block( BLOCK_SIZE );
4937 
4938  const size_t M( A.rows() );
4939  const size_t N( B.columns() );
4940 
4941  for( size_t jj=0UL; jj<N; jj+=block ) {
4942  const size_t jend( min( N, jj+block ) );
4943  for( size_t ii=0UL; ii<M; ii+=block ) {
4944  const size_t iend( min( M, ii+block ) );
4945  for( size_t j=jj; j<jend; ++j )
4946  {
4947  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4948  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j ), ii ) )
4949  :( ii ) );
4950  const size_t ipos( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4951  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL ), iend ) )
4952  :( iend ) );
4953 
4954  if( IsLower<MT4>::value ) {
4955  for( size_t i=ii; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
4956  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4957  }
4958  }
4959  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; ++i ) {
4960  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
4961  }
4962  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
4963  for( size_t i=ipos; i<iend; ++i ) {
4964  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4965  }
4966  }
4967  }
4968  }
4969  }
4970  }

4989  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4990  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4991  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
4992  selectDefaultAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4993  {

4995

4997  const size_t N( B.columns() );
4998 
4999  for( size_t ii=0UL; ii<M; ii+=block ) {
5000  const size_t iend( min( M, ii+block ) );
5001  for( size_t jj=0UL; jj<N; jj+=block ) {
5002  const size_t jend( min( N, jj+block ) );
5003  for( size_t i=ii; i<iend; ++i )
5004  {
5005  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
5006  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+1UL : i ), jj ) )
5007  :( jj ) );

5009  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i : i+1UL ), jend ) )
5010  :( jend ) );

5013  for( size_t j=jj; j<jbegin; ++j ) {
5014  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
5015  }
5016  }
5017  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jpos; ++j ) {
5018  (~C)(i,j) = A(i,i) * B(i,j) * scalar;
5019  }
5020  if( IsLower<MT5>::value ) {

5074  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
5075  reset( (~C)(i,j) );

5125  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix

5127  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5128  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5129  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5130  selectSmallAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5131  {

5134  //**********************************************************************************************
5135 
5136  //**Vectorized default assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)******************
5151  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5152  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5153  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5154  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5155  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5156  selectSmallAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5157  {
5158  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
5159 
5160  const size_t M( A.rows() );
5161  const size_t N( B.columns() );
5162  const size_t K( A.columns() );
5163 
5164  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
5165 
5166  if( LOW && UPP ) {
5167  reset( ~C );
5168  }
5169 
5170  {
5171  size_t i( 0UL );
5172 
5173  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
5174  {
5175  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
5176  size_t j( SYM || HERM || UPP ? i : 0UL );
5177 
5178  for( ; (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
5179  {
5180  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5181  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5182  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5183  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
5184  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+4UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
5185  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+4UL ) : K ) );
5186 
5187  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5188  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5189 
5190  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
5191  size_t k( kbegin );
5192 
5193  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5194  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
5195  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
5196  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
5197  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
5198  const SIMDType b3( B.load(k,j+2UL) );
5199  const SIMDType b4( B.load(k,j+3UL) );
5200  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
5201  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
5202  xmm3 += a1 * b3;
5203  xmm4 += a1 * b4;
5204  xmm5 += a2 * b1;
5205  xmm6 += a2 * b2;
5206  xmm7 += a2 * b3;
5207  xmm8 += a2 * b4;
5208  }
5209 
5210  (~C)(i ,j ) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5211  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5212  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) = sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
5213  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) = sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
5214  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) = sum( xmm5 ) * scalar;
5215  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm6 ) * scalar;
5216  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) = sum( xmm7 ) * scalar;
5217  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) = sum( xmm8 ) * scalar;
5218 
5219  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5220  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5221  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5222  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
5223  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
5224  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5225  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5226  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
5227  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
5228  }
5229  }
5230 
5231  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
5232  {
5233  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5234  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5235  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5236  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
5237  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
5238  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
5239 
5240  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5241  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5242 
5243  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
5244  size_t k( kbegin );
5245 
5246  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5247  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
5248  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
5249  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
5250  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
5251  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
5252  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
5253  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
5254  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
5255  }
5256 
5257  (~C)(i ,j ) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5258  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5259  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) = sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
5260  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
5261 
5262  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5263  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5264  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5265  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5266  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5267  }
5268  }
5269 
5270  if( j < jend )
5271  {
5272  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5273  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5274  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5275  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
5276 
5277  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5278  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5279 
5280  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
5281  size_t k( kbegin );
5282 
5283  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5284  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
5285  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
5286  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
5287  }
5288 
5289  (~C)(i ,j) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5290  (~C)(i+1UL,j) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5291 
5292  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5293  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5294  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5295  }
5296  }
5297  }
5298 
5299  for( ; i<M; ++i )
5300  {
5301  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
5302  size_t j( SYM || HERM || UPP ? i : 0UL );
5303 
5304  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
5305  {
5306  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5307  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5308  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5309  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+4UL ):( K ) );
5310 
5311  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5312  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5313 
5314  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
5315  size_t k( kbegin );
5316 
5317  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5318  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
5319  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
5320  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
5321  xmm3 += a1 * B.load(k,j+2UL);
5322  xmm4 += a1 * B.load(k,j+3UL);
5323  }
5324 
5325  (~C)(i,j ) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5326  (~C)(i,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5327  (~C)(i,j+2UL) = sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
5328  (~C)(i,j+3UL) = sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
5329 
5330  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5331  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5332  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5333  (~C)(i,j+2UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
5334  (~C)(i,j+3UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
5335  }
5336  }
5337 
5338  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
5339  {
5340  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5341  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5342  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5343  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
5344 
5345  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5346  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5347 
5348  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
5349  size_t k( kbegin );
5350 
5351  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5352  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
5353  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
5354  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
5355  }
5356 
5357  (~C)(i,j ) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5358  (~C)(i,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5359 
5360  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5361  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5362  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5363  }
5364  }
5365 
5366  for( ; j<jend; ++j )
5367  {
5368  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5369  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5370  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5371 
5372  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
5373  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5374 
5375  SIMDType xmm1;
5376  size_t k( kbegin );
5377 
5378  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5379  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
5380  }
5381 
5382  (~C)(i,j) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5383 
5384  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
5385  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5386  }
5387  }
5388  }
5389  }
5390 
5391  if( SYM || HERM ) {
5392  for( size_t i=2UL; i<M; ++i ) {
5393  const size_t jend( 2UL * ( i/2UL ) );
5394  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jend; ++j ) {
5395  (~C)(i,j) = HERM ? conj( (~C)(j,i) ) : (~C)(j,i);
5396  }
5397  }
5398  }
5399  else if( LOW && !UPP ) {
5400  for( size_t j=2UL; j<N; ++j ) {
5401  const size_t iend( 2UL * ( j/2UL ) );
5402  for( size_t i=0UL; i<iend; ++i ) {
5403  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
5404  }
5405  }
5406  }
5407  else if( !LOW && UPP ) {
5408  for( size_t i=2UL; i<M; ++i ) {
5409  const size_t jend( 2UL * ( i/2UL ) );
5410  for( size_t j=0UL; j<jend; ++j ) {
5411  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
5412  }
5413  }
5414  }
5415  }
5416  //**********************************************************************************************
5417 
5418  //**Vectorized default assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)***************
5433  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5434  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5435  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5436  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5437  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5438  selectSmallAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5439  {
5440  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
5441 
5442  const size_t M( A.rows() );
5443  const size_t N( B.columns() );
5444  const size_t K( A.columns() );
5445 
5446  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( SYM || HERM || LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
5447 
5448  if( LOW || UPP ) {
5449  reset( ~C );
5450  }
5451 
5452  {
5453  size_t i( 0UL );
5454 
5455  for( ; !SYM && !HERM && !LOW && !UPP && (i+4UL) <= M; i+=4UL )
5456  {
5457  size_t j( 0UL );
5458 
5459  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
5460  {
5461  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5462  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5463  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5464  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
5465  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+4UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+4UL ) )
5466  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
5467 
5468  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5469  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5470 
5471  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
5472  size_t k( kbegin );
5473 
5474  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5475  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
5476  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
5477  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+2UL,k) );
5478  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+3UL,k) );
5479  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
5480  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
5481  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
5482  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
5483  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
5484  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
5485  xmm5 += a3 * b1;
5486  xmm6 += a3 * b2;
5487  xmm7 += a4 * b1;
5488  xmm8 += a4 * b2;
5489  }
5490 
5491  (~C)(i ,j ) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5492  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5493  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) = sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
5494  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
5495  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) = sum( xmm5 ) * scalar;
5496  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm6 ) * scalar;
5497  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) = sum( xmm7 ) * scalar;
5498  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm8 ) * scalar;
5499 
5500  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5501  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5502  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5503  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5504  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5505  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5506  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5507  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5508  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5509  }
5510  }
5511 
5512  if( j < N )
5513  {
5514  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5515  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5516  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5517  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+4UL ):( K ) );
5518 
5519  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5520  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5521 
5522  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
5523  size_t k( kbegin );
5524 
5525  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5526  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
5527  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
5528  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
5529  xmm3 += A.load(i+2UL,k) * b1;
5530  xmm4 += A.load(i+3UL,k) * b1;
5531  }
5532 
5533  (~C)(i ,j) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5534  (~C)(i+1UL,j) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5535  (~C)(i+2UL,j) = sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
5536  (~C)(i+3UL,j) = sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
5537 
5538  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5539  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5540  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5541  (~C)(i+2UL,j) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5542  (~C)(i+3UL,j) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5543  }
5544  }
5545  }
5546 
5547  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
5548  {
5549  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
5550  size_t j( SYM || HERM || UPP ? i : 0UL );
5551 
5552  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
5553  {
5554  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5555  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5556  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5557  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
5558  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
5559  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
5560 
5561  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5562  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5563 
5564  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
5565  size_t k( kbegin );
5566 
5567  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5568  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
5569  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
5570  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
5571  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
5572  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
5573  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
5574  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
5575  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
5576  }
5577 
5578  (~C)(i ,j ) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5579  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5580  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) = sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
5581  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) = sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
5582 
5583  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5584  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5585  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5586  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5587  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5588  }
5589  }
5590 
5591  if( j < jend )
5592  {
5593  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5594  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5595  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5596  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
5597 
5598  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5599  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5600 
5601  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
5602  size_t k( kbegin );
5603 
5604  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5605  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
5606  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
5607  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
5608  }
5609 
5610  (~C)(i ,j) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5611  (~C)(i+1UL,j) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5612 
5613  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5614  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5615  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5616  }
5617  }
5618  }
5619 
5620  if( i < M )
5621  {
5622  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
5623  size_t j( SYM || HERM || UPP ? i : 0UL );
5624 
5625  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
5626  {
5627  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5628  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5629  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5630  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
5631 
5632  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
5633  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5634 
5635  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
5636  size_t k( kbegin );
5637 
5638  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5639  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
5640  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
5641  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
5642  }
5643 
5644  (~C)(i,j ) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5645  (~C)(i,j+1UL) = sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
5646 
5647  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
5648  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
5649  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
5650  }
5651  }
5652 
5653  if( j < jend )
5654  {
5655  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5656  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
5657  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
5658 
5659  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
5660  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5661 
5662  SIMDType xmm1;
5663  size_t k( kbegin );
5664 
5665  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
5666  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
5667  }
5668 
5669  (~C)(i,j) = sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
5670 
5671  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
5672  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
5673  }
5674  }
5675  }
5676  }
5677 
5678  if( SYM || HERM ) {
5679  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j ) {
5680  for( size_t i=j+1UL; i<M; ++i ) {
5681  (~C)(i,j) = HERM ? conj( (~C)(j,i) ) : (~C)(j,i);
5682  }
5683  }
5684  }
5685  }

5688  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)***************************************
5702  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5703  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5704  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5705  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5706  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5707  selectLargeAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5708  {
5709  selectDefaultAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5710  }
5711  //**********************************************************************************************
5712 
5713  //**Vectorized default assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)****************************
5728  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5729  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5730  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5731  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5732  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5733  selectLargeAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5734  {
5735  if( SYM )
5736  smmm( C, A, B, scalar );
5737  else if( HERM )
5738  hmmm( C, A, B, scalar );
5739  else if( LOW )
5740  lmmm( C, A, B, scalar, ST2(0) );
5741  else if( UPP )
5742  ummm( C, A, B, scalar, ST2(0) );
5743  else
5744  mmm( C, A, B, scalar, ST2(0) );
5745  }
5746  //**********************************************************************************************
5747 
5748  //**BLAS-based assignment to dense matrices (default)*******************************************
5762  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5763  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5764  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5765  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5766  static inline DisableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5767  selectBlasAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5768  {
5769  selectLargeAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5770  }
5771  //**********************************************************************************************
5772 
5773  //**BLAS-based assignment to dense matrices*****************************************************
5774 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
5775 
5788  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5789  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5790  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5791  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5792  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5793  selectBlasAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5794  {
5795  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
5796 
5797  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
5798  assign( C, B );
5799  trmm( C, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
5800  }
5801  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
5802  assign( C, A );
5803  trmm( C, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
5804  }
5805  else {
5806  gemm( C, A, B, ET(scalar), ET(0) );
5807  }
5808  }
5809 #endif
5810  //**********************************************************************************************
5811 
5812  //**Assignment to sparse matrices***************************************************************
5824  template< typename MT // Type of the target sparse matrix
5825  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target sparse matrix
5826  friend inline void assign( SparseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
5827  {
5828  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
5829 
5830  typedef IfTrue_< SO, OppositeType, ResultType > TmpType;
5831 
5832  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
5833  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
5834  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
5835  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
5836  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MATRICES_MUST_HAVE_SAME_STORAGE_ORDER( MT, TmpType );
5837  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_REFERENCE_TYPE( CompositeType_<TmpType> );
5838 
5839  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5840  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5841 
5842  const ForwardFunctor fwd;
5843 
5844  const TmpType tmp( serial( rhs ) );
5845  assign( ~lhs, fwd( tmp ) );
5846  }

5848 
5849  //**Addition assignment to dense matrices*******************************************************
5861  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
5862  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
5863  friend inline void addAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
5864  {
5865  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
5866 
5867  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5868  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5869 
5870  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
5871  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
5872 
5873  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || left.columns() == 0UL ) {
5874  return;
5875  }
5876 
5877  LT A( serial( left ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
5878  RT B( serial( right ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
5879 
5880  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5881  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
5882  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5883  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
5884  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5885  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5886 
5887  DMatScalarMultExpr::selectAddAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B, rhs.scalar_ );
5888  }
5889  //**********************************************************************************************
5890 
5891  //**Addition assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)************************************
5902  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5903  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5904  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5905  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5906  static inline void selectAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5907  {
5908  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value || IsDiagonal<MT5>::value ) ||
5909  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < DMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
5910  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5911  else
5912  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5913  }

5916  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (general/general)*****************************
5930  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5931  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5932  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5933  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5934  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
5935  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5936  {
5937  const ResultType tmp( serial( A * B * scalar ) );
5938  addAssign( C, tmp );
5939  }

5942  //**Default addition assignment to row-major dense matrices (general/diagonal)******************
5956  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5957  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5958  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5959  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5960  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
5961  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5962  {
5963  const size_t M( A.rows() );
5964  const size_t N( B.columns() );
5965 
5966  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i )
5967  {
5968  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5969  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
5970  :( 0UL ) );
5971  const size_t jend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
5972  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
5973  :( N ) );
5974  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
5975 
5976  const size_t jnum( jend - jbegin );
5977  const size_t jpos( jbegin + ( jnum & size_t(-2) ) );
5978 
5979  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jpos; j+=2UL ) {
5980  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,j ) * B(j ,j ) * scalar;
5981  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,j+1UL) * B(j+1UL,j+1UL) * scalar;
5982  }
5983  if( jpos < jend ) {
5984  (~C)(i,jpos) += A(i,jpos) * B(jpos,jpos) * scalar;
5985  }
5986  }
5987  }

5990  //**Default addition assignment to column-major dense matrices (general/diagonal)***************
6004  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6005  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6006  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6007  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6008  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
6009  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6010  {
6011  constexpr size_t block( BLOCK_SIZE );
6012 
6013  const size_t M( A.rows() );
6014  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6015 
6016  for( size_t jj=0UL; jj<N; jj+=block ) {
6017  const size_t jend( min( N, jj+block ) );
6018  for( size_t ii=0UL; ii<M; ii+=block ) {
6019  const size_t iend( min( M, ii+block ) );
6020  for( size_t j=jj; j<jend; ++j )
6021  {
6022  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6023  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j ), ii ) )
6024  :( ii ) );
6025  const size_t ipos( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6026  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL ), iend ) )
6027  :( iend ) );
6028 
6029  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; ++i ) {
6030  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
6031  }
6032  }
6033  }
6034  }
6035  }

6065  const size_t iend( min( M, ii+block ) );

6067  const size_t jend( min( N, jj+block ) );
6068  for( size_t i=ii; i<iend; ++i )
6069  {
6070  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6071  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+1UL : i ), jj ) )
6072  :( jj ) );
6073  const size_t jpos( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6074  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i : i+1UL ), jend ) )
6075  :( jend ) );

6078  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,i) * B(i,j) * scalar;
6079  }
6080  }

6100  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6101  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6102  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6103  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6104  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
6105  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6106  {

6108  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6109 
6110  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
6111  {
6112  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6113  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
6114  :( 0UL ) );
6115  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6116  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
6117  :( M ) );
6118  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
6119 
6120  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
6121  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
6122 
6123  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
6124  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,i ) * B(i ,j) * scalar;
6125  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,i+1UL) * B(i+1UL,j) * scalar;
6126  }
6127  if( ipos < iend ) {
6128  (~C)(ipos,j) += A(ipos,ipos) * B(ipos,j) * scalar;
6129  }
6130  }

6186  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)*********
6201  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6202  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6203  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6204  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6205  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
6206  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6207  {
6208  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
6209 
6210  const size_t M( A.rows() );
6211  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6212  const size_t K( A.columns() );
6213 
6214  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
6215 
6216  size_t i( 0UL );
6217 
6218  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
6219  {
6220  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
6221  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
6222 
6223  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
6224  {
6225  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6226  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6227  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6228  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6229  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+4UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
6230  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+4UL ) : K ) );
6231 
6232  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6233  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6234 
6235  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
6236  size_t k( kbegin );
6237 
6238  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6239  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
6240  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
6241  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
6242  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
6243  const SIMDType b3( B.load(k,j+2UL) );
6244  const SIMDType b4( B.load(k,j+3UL) );
6245  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
6246  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
6247  xmm3 += a1 * b3;
6248  xmm4 += a1 * b4;
6249  xmm5 += a2 * b1;
6250  xmm6 += a2 * b2;
6251  xmm7 += a2 * b3;
6252  xmm8 += a2 * b4;
6253  }
6254 
6255  (~C)(i ,j ) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6256  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6257  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) += sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
6258  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) += sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
6259  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += sum( xmm5 ) * scalar;
6260  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm6 ) * scalar;
6261  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) += sum( xmm7 ) * scalar;
6262  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) += sum( xmm8 ) * scalar;
6263 
6264  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6265  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6266  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6267  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
6268  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
6269  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6270  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6271  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
6272  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
6273  }
6274  }
6275 
6276  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
6277  {
6278  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6279  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6280  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6281  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6282  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
6283  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
6284 
6285  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6286  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6287 
6288  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
6289  size_t k( kbegin );
6290 
6291  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6292  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
6293  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
6294  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
6295  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
6296  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
6297  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
6298  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
6299  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
6300  }
6301 
6302  (~C)(i ,j ) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6303  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6304  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
6305  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
6306 
6307  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6308  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6309  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6310  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6311  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6312  }
6313  }
6314 
6315  if( j < jend )
6316  {
6317  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6318  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6319  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6320  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
6321 
6322  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6323  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6324 
6325  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
6326  size_t k( kbegin );
6327 
6328  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6329  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
6330  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
6331  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
6332  }
6333 
6334  (~C)(i ,j) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6335  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6336 
6337  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6338  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6339  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6340  }
6341  }
6342  }
6343 
6344  if( i < M )
6345  {
6346  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
6347  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
6348 
6349  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
6350  {
6351  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6352  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6353  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6354  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+4UL ):( K ) );
6355 
6356  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6357  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6358 
6359  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
6360  size_t k( kbegin );
6361 
6362  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6363  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
6364  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
6365  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
6366  xmm3 += a1 * B.load(k,j+2UL);
6367  xmm4 += a1 * B.load(k,j+3UL);
6368  }
6369 
6370  (~C)(i,j ) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6371  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6372  (~C)(i,j+2UL) += sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
6373  (~C)(i,j+3UL) += sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
6374 
6375  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6376  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6377  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6378  (~C)(i,j+2UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
6379  (~C)(i,j+3UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
6380  }
6381  }
6382 
6383  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
6384  {
6385  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6386  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6387  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6388  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
6389 
6390  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6391  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6392 
6393  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
6394  size_t k( kbegin );
6395 
6396  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6397  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
6398  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
6399  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
6400  }

6403  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6404 
6405  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6406  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6407  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6408  }
6409  }
6410 
6411  if( j < jend )
6412  {
6413  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6414  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6415  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6416 
6417  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
6418  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6419 
6420  SIMDType xmm1;

6424  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);

6428

6430  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6431  }
6432  }
6433  }
