6437  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)******
6452  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6453  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6454  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6455  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6456  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
6457  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6458  {
6459  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
6460 
6461  const size_t M( A.rows() );
6462  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6463  const size_t K( A.columns() );
6464 
6465  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
6466 
6467  size_t i( 0UL );
6468 
6469  for( ; !LOW && !UPP && (i+4UL) <= M; i+=4UL )
6470  {
6471  size_t j( 0UL );
6472 
6473  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
6474  {
6475  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6476  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6477  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6478  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6479  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+4UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+4UL ) )
6480  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
6481 
6482  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6483  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6484 
6485  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
6486  size_t k( kbegin );
6487 
6488  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6489  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
6490  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
6491  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+2UL,k) );
6492  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+3UL,k) );
6493  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
6494  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
6495  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
6496  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
6497  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
6498  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
6499  xmm5 += a3 * b1;
6500  xmm6 += a3 * b2;
6501  xmm7 += a4 * b1;
6502  xmm8 += a4 * b2;
6503  }
6504 
6505  (~C)(i ,j ) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6506  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6507  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
6508  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
6509  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) += sum( xmm5 ) * scalar;
6510  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm6 ) * scalar;
6511  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) += sum( xmm7 ) * scalar;
6512  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm8 ) * scalar;
6513 
6514  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6515  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6516  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6517  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6518  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6519  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6520  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6521  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6522  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6523  }
6524  }
6525 
6526  if( j < N )
6527  {
6528  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6529  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6530  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6531  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+4UL ):( K ) );
6532 
6533  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6534  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6535 
6536  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
6537  size_t k( kbegin );
6538 
6539  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6540  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
6541  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
6542  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
6543  xmm3 += A.load(i+2UL,k) * b1;
6544  xmm4 += A.load(i+3UL,k) * b1;
6545  }
6546 
6547  (~C)(i ,j) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6548  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6549  (~C)(i+2UL,j) += sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
6550  (~C)(i+3UL,j) += sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
6551 
6552  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6553  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6554  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6555  (~C)(i+2UL,j) += A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6556  (~C)(i+3UL,j) += A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6557  }
6558  }
6559  }
6560 
6561  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
6562  {
6563  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
6564  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
6565 
6566  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
6567  {
6568  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6569  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6570  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6571  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6572  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
6573  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
6574 
6575  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6576  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6577 
6578  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
6579  size_t k( kbegin );
6580 
6581  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6582  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
6583  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
6584  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
6585  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
6586  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
6587  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
6588  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
6589  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
6590  }
6591 
6592  (~C)(i ,j ) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6593  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6594  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
6595  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
6596 
6597  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6598  (~C)(i ,j ) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6599  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6600  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6601  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6602  }
6603  }
6604 
6605  if( j < jend )
6606  {
6607  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6608  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6609  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6610  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
6611 
6612  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6613  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6614 
6615  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
6616  size_t k( kbegin );
6617 
6618  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6619  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
6620  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
6621  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
6622  }
6623 
6624  (~C)(i ,j) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6625  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6626 
6627  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6628  (~C)(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6629  (~C)(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6630  }
6631  }
6632  }
6633 
6634  if( i < M )
6635  {
6636  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
6637  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
6638 
6639  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
6640  {
6641  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6642  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6643  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6644  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
6645 
6646  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
6647  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6648 
6649  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
6650  size_t k( kbegin );
6651 
6652  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6653  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
6654  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
6655  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
6656  }
6657 
6658  (~C)(i,j ) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6659  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
6660 
6661  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
6662  (~C)(i,j ) += A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
6663  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
6664  }
6665  }
6666 
6667  if( j < jend )
6668  {
6669  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6670  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
6671  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
6672 
6673  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
6674  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6675 
6676  SIMDType xmm1;
6677  size_t k( kbegin );
6678 
6679  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
6680  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
6681  }
6682 
6683  (~C)(i,j) += sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
6684 
6685  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
6686  (~C)(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
6687  }
6688  }
6689  }
6690  }

6789  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6790  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6791  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6792  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6793  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
6794  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6795  {

6797

6799  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( B ) );
6800  trmm( tmp, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
6801  addAssign( C, tmp );
6802  }
6803  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
6804  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( A ) );
6805  trmm( tmp, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
6806  addAssign( C, tmp );
6807  }
6808  else {
6809  gemm( C, A, B, ET(scalar), ET(1) );
6810  }
6811  }
6812 #endif

6819  //**Subtraction assignment to dense matrices****************************************************
6831  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
6832  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
6833  friend inline void subAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
6834  {
6835  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
6836 
6837  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6838  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
6839 
6840  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
6841  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
6842 
6843  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || left.columns() == 0UL ) {
6844  return;
6845  }
6846 
6847  LT A( serial( left ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
6848  RT B( serial( right ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
6849 
6850  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6851  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
6852  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6853  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
6854  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6855  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
6856 
6857  DMatScalarMultExpr::selectSubAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B, rhs.scalar_ );
6858  }

6860 
6861  //**Subtraction assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)*********************************
6872  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6873  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6874  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6875  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6876  static inline void selectSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6877  {
6878  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value || IsDiagonal<MT5>::value ) ||
6879  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < DMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
6880  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
6881  else
6882  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
6883  }

6886  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (general/general)**************************
6900  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6901  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6902  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6903  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6904  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
6905  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )

6912  //**Default subtraction assignment to row-major dense matrices (general/diagonal)***************
6926  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6927  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6928  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6929  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6930  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
6931  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6932  {
6933  const size_t M( A.rows() );
6934  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6935 
6936  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i )
6937  {
6938  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6939  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? i+1UL : i )
6940  :( 0UL ) );
6941  const size_t jend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6942  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? i : i+1UL )
6943  :( N ) );
6944  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( jbegin <= jend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
6945 
6946  const size_t jnum( jend - jbegin );
6947  const size_t jpos( jbegin + ( jnum & size_t(-2) ) );
6948 
6949  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jpos; j+=2UL ) {
6950  (~C)(i,j ) -= A(i,j ) * B(j ,j ) * scalar;
6951  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= A(i,j+1UL) * B(j+1UL,j+1UL) * scalar;
6952  }
6953  if( jpos < jend ) {
6954  (~C)(i,jpos) -= A(i,jpos) * B(jpos,jpos) * scalar;
6955  }
6956  }
6957  }
6958  //**********************************************************************************************
6959 
6960  //**Default subtraction assignment to column-major dense matrices (general/diagonal)************
6974  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6975  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6976  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6977  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6978  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
6979  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6980  {
6981  constexpr size_t block( BLOCK_SIZE );
6982 
6983  const size_t M( A.rows() );
6984  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6985 
6986  for( size_t jj=0UL; jj<N; jj+=block ) {
6987  const size_t jend( min( N, jj+block ) );
6988  for( size_t ii=0UL; ii<M; ii+=block ) {
6989  const size_t iend( min( M, ii+block ) );
6990  for( size_t j=jj; j<jend; ++j )
6991  {
6992  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6993  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j ), ii ) )
6994  :( ii ) );
6995  const size_t ipos( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6996  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL ), iend ) )
6997  :( iend ) );
6998 
6999  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; ++i ) {
7000  (~C)(i,j) -= A(i,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
7001  }
7002  }
7003  }
7004  }
7005  }

7008  //**Default subtraction assignment to row-major dense matrices (diagonal/general)***************
7023  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7024  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7025  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7026  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7027  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
7028  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7029  {
7030  constexpr size_t block( BLOCK_SIZE );
7031 
7032  const size_t M( A.rows() );
7033  const size_t N( B.columns() );
7034 
7035  for( size_t ii=0UL; ii<M; ii+=block ) {
7036  const size_t iend( min( M, ii+block ) );
7037  for( size_t jj=0UL; jj<N; jj+=block ) {
7038  const size_t jend( min( N, jj+block ) );
7039  for( size_t i=ii; i<iend; ++i )
7040  {
7041  const size_t jbegin( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
7042  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? i+1UL : i ), jj ) )
7043  :( jj ) );
7044  const size_t jpos( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
7045  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? i : i+1UL ), jend ) )
7046  :( jend ) );
7047 
7048  for( size_t j=jbegin; j<jpos; ++j ) {
7049  (~C)(i,j) -= A(i,i) * B(i,j) * scalar;
7050  }
7051  }
7052  }
7053  }
7054  }
7055  //**********************************************************************************************
7056 
7057  //**Default subtraction assignment to column-major dense matrices (diagonal/general)************
7072  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7073  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7074  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7075  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7076  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
7077  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7078  {
7079  const size_t M( A.rows() );
7080  const size_t N( B.columns() );
7081 
7082  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
7083  {
7084  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
7085  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
7086  :( 0UL ) );
7087  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
7088  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
7089  :( M ) );
7090  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
7091 
7092  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
7093  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
7094 
7095  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
7096  (~C)(i ,j) -= A(i ,i ) * B(i ,j) * scalar;
7097  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,i+1UL) * B(i+1UL,j) * scalar;
7098  }
7099  if( ipos < iend ) {
7100  (~C)(ipos,j) -= A(ipos,ipos) * B(ipos,j) * scalar;
7101  }
7102  }
7103  }
7104  //**********************************************************************************************
7105 
7106  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/diagonal)************************
7120  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7121  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7122  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7123  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7124  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
7125  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7126  {
7127  for( size_t i=0UL; i<A.rows(); ++i ) {
7128  C(i,i) -= A(i,i) * B(i,i) * scalar;
7129  }
7130  }
7131  //**********************************************************************************************
7132 
7133  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (small matrices)***************************
7147  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7148  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7149  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7150  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7151  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
7152  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7153  {
7154  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
7155  }
7156  //**********************************************************************************************
7157 
7158  //**Vectorized default subtraction assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)******
7173  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7174  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7175  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7176  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7177  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
7178  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7179  {
7180  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
7181 
7182  const size_t M( A.rows() );
7183  const size_t N( B.columns() );
7184  const size_t K( A.columns() );
7185 
7186  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
7187 
7188  size_t i( 0UL );
7189 
7190  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
7191  {
7192  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
7193  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
7194 
7195  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
7196  {
7197  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7198  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7199  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7200  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
7201  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+4UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
7202  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+4UL ) : K ) );
7203 
7204  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7205  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7206 
7207  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
7208  size_t k( kbegin );
7209 
7210  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7211  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
7212  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
7213  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
7214  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
7215  const SIMDType b3( B.load(k,j+2UL) );
7216  const SIMDType b4( B.load(k,j+3UL) );
7217  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
7218  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
7219  xmm3 += a1 * b3;
7220  xmm4 += a1 * b4;
7221  xmm5 += a2 * b1;
7222  xmm6 += a2 * b2;
7223  xmm7 += a2 * b3;
7224  xmm8 += a2 * b4;
7225  }
7226 
7227  (~C)(i ,j ) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7228  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7229  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) -= sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
7230  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) -= sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
7231  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= sum( xmm5 ) * scalar;
7232  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm6 ) * scalar;
7233  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) -= sum( xmm7 ) * scalar;
7234  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) -= sum( xmm8 ) * scalar;
7235 
7236  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7237  (~C)(i ,j ) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7238  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7239  (~C)(i ,j+2UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
7240  (~C)(i ,j+3UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
7241  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7242  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7243  (~C)(i+1UL,j+2UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
7244  (~C)(i+1UL,j+3UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
7245  }
7246  }
7247 
7248  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
7249  {
7250  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7251  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7252  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7253  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
7254  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
7255  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
7256 
7257  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7258  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7259 
7260  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
7261  size_t k( kbegin );
7262 
7263  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7264  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
7265  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
7266  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
7267  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
7268  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
7269  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
7270  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
7271  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
7272  }
7273 
7274  (~C)(i ,j ) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7275  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7276  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
7277  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
7278 
7279  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7280  (~C)(i ,j ) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7281  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7282  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7283  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7284  }
7285  }
7286 
7287  if( j < jend )
7288  {
7289  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7290  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7291  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7292  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
7293 
7294  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7295  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7296 
7297  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
7298  size_t k( kbegin );
7299 
7300  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7301  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
7302  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
7303  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
7304  }
7305 
7306  (~C)(i ,j) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7307  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7308 
7309  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7310  (~C)(i ,j) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7311  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7312  }
7313  }
7314  }
7315 
7316  if( i < M )
7317  {
7318  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
7319  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
7320 
7321  for( ; !( LOW && UPP ) && (j+4UL) <= jend; j+=4UL )
7322  {
7323  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7324  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7325  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7326  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+4UL ):( K ) );
7327 
7328  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7329  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7330 
7331  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
7332  size_t k( kbegin );
7333 
7334  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7335  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
7336  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
7337  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
7338  xmm3 += a1 * B.load(k,j+2UL);
7339  xmm4 += a1 * B.load(k,j+3UL);
7340  }
7341 
7342  (~C)(i,j ) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7343  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7344  (~C)(i,j+2UL) -= sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
7345  (~C)(i,j+3UL) -= sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
7346 
7347  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7348  (~C)(i,j ) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7349  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7350  (~C)(i,j+2UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+2UL) * scalar;
7351  (~C)(i,j+3UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+3UL) * scalar;
7352  }
7353  }
7354 
7355  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
7356  {
7357  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7358  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7359  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7360  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
7361 
7362  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7363  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7364 
7365  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
7366  size_t k( kbegin );
7367 
7368  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7369  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
7370  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
7371  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
7372  }
7373 
7374  (~C)(i,j ) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7375  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7376 
7377  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7378  (~C)(i,j ) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7379  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7380  }
7381  }
7382 
7383  if( j < jend )
7384  {
7385  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7386  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7387  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7388 
7389  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
7390  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7391 
7392  SIMDType xmm1;
7393  size_t k( kbegin );
7394 
7395  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7396  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
7397  }
7398 
7399  (~C)(i,j) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7400 
7401  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
7402  (~C)(i,j) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7403  }
7404  }
7405  }
7406  }

7409  //**Vectorized default subtraction assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)***
7424  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7425  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7426  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7427  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7428  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
7429  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7430  {
7431  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT4>::value || !IsPadded<MT5>::value );
7432 
7433  const size_t M( A.rows() );
7434  const size_t N( B.columns() );
7435  const size_t K( A.columns() );
7436 
7437  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !( LOW || UPP ) || ( M == N ), "Broken invariant detected" );
7438 
7439  size_t i( 0UL );
7440 
7441  for( ; !LOW && !UPP && (i+4UL) <= M; i+=4UL )
7442  {
7443  size_t j( 0UL );
7444 
7445  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
7446  {
7447  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7448  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7449  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7450  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
7451  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+4UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+4UL ) )
7452  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
7453 
7454  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7455  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7456 
7457  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
7458  size_t k( kbegin );
7459 
7460  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE )
7461  {
7462  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
7463  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
7464  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+2UL,k) );
7465  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+3UL,k) );
7466  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
7467  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
7468  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
7469  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
7470  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
7471  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
7472  xmm5 += a3 * b1;
7473  xmm6 += a3 * b2;
7474  xmm7 += a4 * b1;
7475  xmm8 += a4 * b2;
7476  }
7477 
7478  (~C)(i ,j ) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7479  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7480  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
7481  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
7482  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) -= sum( xmm5 ) * scalar;
7483  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm6 ) * scalar;
7484  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) -= sum( xmm7 ) * scalar;
7485  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm8 ) * scalar;
7486 
7487  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7488  (~C)(i ,j ) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7489  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7490  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7491  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7492  (~C)(i+2UL,j ) -= A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7493  (~C)(i+2UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7494  (~C)(i+3UL,j ) -= A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7495  (~C)(i+3UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7496  }
7497  }
7498 
7499  if( j < N )
7500  {
7501  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7502  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7503  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7504  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+4UL ):( K ) );
7505 
7506  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7507  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7508 
7509  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
7510  size_t k( kbegin );
7511 
7512  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7513  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
7514  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
7515  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
7516  xmm3 += A.load(i+2UL,k) * b1;
7517  xmm4 += A.load(i+3UL,k) * b1;
7518  }
7519 
7520  (~C)(i ,j) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7521  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7522  (~C)(i+2UL,j) -= sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
7523  (~C)(i+3UL,j) -= sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
7524 
7525  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7526  (~C)(i ,j) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7527  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7528  (~C)(i+2UL,j) -= A(i+2UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7529  (~C)(i+3UL,j) -= A(i+3UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7530  }
7531  }
7532  }
7533 
7534  for( ; (i+2UL) <= M; i+=2UL )
7535  {
7536  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+2UL : N );
7537  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
7538 
7539  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
7540  {
7541  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7542  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7543  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7544  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
7545  ?( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? min( i+2UL, j+2UL ) : ( i+2UL ) )
7546  :( IsUpper<MT5>::value ? ( j+2UL ) : K ) );
7547 
7548  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7549  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7550 
7551  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
7552  size_t k( kbegin );
7553 
7554  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7555  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
7556  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+1UL,k) );
7557  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j ) );
7558  const SIMDType b2( B.load(k,j+1UL) );
7559  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
7560  xmm2 += a1 * b2;
7561  xmm3 += a2 * b1;
7562  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
7563  }
7564 
7565  (~C)(i ,j ) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7566  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7567  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= sum( xmm3 ) * scalar;
7568  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm4 ) * scalar;
7569 
7570  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7571  (~C)(i ,j ) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7572  (~C)(i ,j+1UL) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7573  (~C)(i+1UL,j ) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7574  (~C)(i+1UL,j+1UL) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7575  }
7576  }
7577 
7578  if( j < jend )
7579  {
7580  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7581  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7582  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7583  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( i+2UL ):( K ) );
7584 
7585  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7586  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7587 
7588  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
7589  size_t k( kbegin );
7590 
7591  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7592  const SIMDType b1( B.load(k,j) );
7593  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
7594  xmm2 += A.load(i+1UL,k) * b1;
7595  }
7596 
7597  (~C)(i ,j) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7598  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7599 
7600  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7601  (~C)(i ,j) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7602  (~C)(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7603  }
7604  }
7605  }
7606 
7607  if( i < M )
7608  {
7609  const size_t jend( LOW ? i+1UL : N );
7610  size_t j( UPP ? i : 0UL );
7611 
7612  for( ; (j+2UL) <= jend; j+=2UL )
7613  {
7614  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7615  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7616  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7617  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )?( j+2UL ):( K ) );
7618 
7619  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( kend & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : kend );
7620  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( kend - ( kend % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7621 
7622  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
7623  size_t k( kbegin );
7624 
7625  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7626  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
7627  xmm1 += a1 * B.load(k,j );
7628  xmm2 += a1 * B.load(k,j+1UL);
7629  }
7630 
7631  (~C)(i,j ) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7632  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= sum( xmm2 ) * scalar;
7633 
7634  for( ; remainder && k<kend; ++k ) {
7635  (~C)(i,j ) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j ) * scalar;
7636  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL) * scalar;
7637  }
7638  }
7639 
7640  if( j < jend )
7641  {
7642  const size_t kbegin( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
7643  ?( ( IsLower<MT5>::value ? max( i, j ) : i ) & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) )
7644  :( IsLower<MT5>::value ? ( j & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : 0UL ) );
7645 
7646  const size_t kpos( remainder ? ( K & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : K );
7647  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( K - ( K % (SIMDSIZE) ) ) == kpos, "Invalid end calculation" );
7648 
7649  SIMDType xmm1;
7650  size_t k( kbegin );
7651 
7652  for( ; k<kpos; k+=SIMDSIZE ) {
7653  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * B.load(k,j);
7654  }
7655 
7656  (~C)(i,j) -= sum( xmm1 ) * scalar;
7657 
7658  for( ; remainder && k<K; ++k ) {
7659  (~C)(i,j) -= A(i,k) * B(k,j) * scalar;
7660  }
7661  }
7662  }
7663  }
7664  //**********************************************************************************************
7665 
7666  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)***************************
7680  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7681  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7682  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7683  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7684  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
7685  selectLargeSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7686  {
7687  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
7688  }
7689  //**********************************************************************************************
7690 
7691  //**Vectorized default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)****************
7706  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7707  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7708  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7709  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7710  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
7711  selectLargeSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7712  {
7713  if( LOW )
7714  lmmm( C, A, B, -scalar, ST2(1) );
7715  else if( UPP )
7716  ummm( C, A, B, -scalar, ST2(1) );
7717  else
7718  mmm( C, A, B, -scalar, ST2(1) );
7719  }
7720  //**********************************************************************************************
7721 
7722  //**BLAS-based subtraction assignment to dense matrices (default)*******************************
7736  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7737  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7738  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7739  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7740  static inline DisableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
7741  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7742  {
7743  selectLargeSubAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
7744  }
7745  //**********************************************************************************************
7746 
7747  //**BLAS-based subraction assignment to dense matrices******************************************
7748 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
7749 
7762  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
7763  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
7764  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
7765  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
7766  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
7767  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
7768  {
7769  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
7770 
7771  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
7772  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( B ) );
7773  trmm( tmp, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
7774  subAssign( C, tmp );
7775  }
7776  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
7777  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( A ) );
7778  trmm( tmp, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
7779  subAssign( C, tmp );
7780  }
7781  else {
7782  gemm( C, A, B, ET(-scalar), ET(1) );
7783  }
7784  }
7785 #endif
7786  //**********************************************************************************************

7789  // No special implementation for the subtraction assignment to sparse matrices.
7790  //**********************************************************************************************
7791

7793  // No special implementation for the multiplication assignment to dense matrices.

7800  //**SMP assignment to dense matrices************************************************************
7815  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
7816  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
7817  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
7818  smpAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
7819  {
7820  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
7821 
7822  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7823  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
7824 
7825  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
7826  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
7827 
7828  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL ) {
7829  return;
7830  }
7831  else if( left.columns() == 0UL ) {
7832  reset( ~lhs );
7833  return;
7834  }
7835 
7836  LT A( left ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
7837  RT B( right ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
7838 
7839  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7840  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
7841  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7842  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
7843  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7844  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
7845 
7846  smpAssign( ~lhs, A * B * rhs.scalar_ );
7847  }
7848  //**********************************************************************************************
7849 
7850  //**SMP assignment to sparse matrices***********************************************************
7865  template< typename MT // Type of the target sparse matrix
7866  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target sparse matrix
7867  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
7868  smpAssign( SparseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
7869  {
7870  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
7871 
7872  typedef IfTrue_< SO, OppositeType, ResultType > TmpType;
7873 
7874  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
7875  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
7876  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
7877  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
7878  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MATRICES_MUST_HAVE_SAME_STORAGE_ORDER( MT, TmpType );
7879  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_REFERENCE_TYPE( CompositeType_<TmpType> );
7880 
7881  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7882  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
7883 
7884  const ForwardFunctor fwd;
7885 
7886  const TmpType tmp( rhs );
7887  smpAssign( ~lhs, fwd( tmp ) );
7888  }
7889  //**********************************************************************************************
7890

7906  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
7907  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
7908  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
7909  smpAddAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
7910  {

7912

7915

7917  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
7918 
7919  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || left.columns() == 0UL ) {
7920  return;
7921  }
7922 
7923  LT A( left ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
7924  RT B( right ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
7925 
7926  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7927  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
7928  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7929  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
7930  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7931  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
7932 
7933  smpAddAssign( ~lhs, A * B * rhs.scalar_ );
7934  }

7941  //**SMP subtraction assignment to dense matrices************************************************
7956  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
7957  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
7958  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
7959  smpSubAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
7960  {

7962

7964  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
7965

7967  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
7968 
7969  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || left.columns() == 0UL ) {
7970  return;
7971  }
7972 
7973  LT A( left ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
7974  RT B( right ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
7975 
7976  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7977  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
7978  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7979  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
7980  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7981  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
7982

7992  // No special implementation for the SMP multiplication assignment to dense matrices.
7993  //**********************************************************************************************
7994 
7995  //**SMP multiplication assignment to sparse matrices********************************************
7996  // No special implementation for the SMP multiplication assignment to sparse matrices.
7997  //**********************************************************************************************
7998 
7999  //**Compile time checks*************************************************************************
8000  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( MMM );
8001  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MMM );
8002  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( MT1 );
8003  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT1 );
8004  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( MT2 );
8005  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT2 );
8006  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_NUMERIC_TYPE( ST );
8007  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_SAME_TYPE( ST, RightOperand );
8008  //**********************************************************************************************
8009 };

8052 template< typename T1 // Type of the left-hand side dense matrix
8053  , typename T2 > // Type of the right-hand side dense matrix
8054 inline const DMatTDMatMultExpr<T1,T2,false,false,false,false>
8055  operator*( const DenseMatrix<T1,false>& lhs, const DenseMatrix<T2,true>& rhs )
8056 {
8057  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
8058 
8059  if( (~lhs).columns() != (~rhs).rows() ) {
8060  BLAZE_THROW_INVALID_ARGUMENT( "Matrix sizes do not match" );
8061  }
8062 
8063  return DMatTDMatMultExpr<T1,T2,false,false,false,false>( ~lhs, ~rhs );
8064 }

Type relationship analysis.This class tests if the two data types A and B are equal. For this type comparison, the cv-qualifiers of both data types are ignored. If A and B are the same data type (ignoring the cv-qualifiers), then the value member constant is set to true, the nested type definition Type is TrueType, and the class derives from TrueType.
